WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.081 --> 00:00:04.794
Subtitles by explosiveskull
www.OpenSubtitles.org


2
00:00:29.410 --> 00:00:31.718
In my little heimat,

3
00:00:31.720 --> 00:00:36.180
one can sense similar feelings
to being on an island,


4
00:00:37.220 --> 00:00:42.220
safety, a sense of
security, real or fictional,


5
00:00:42.260 --> 00:00:44.818
and of remoteness.

6
00:00:44.820 --> 00:00:47.838
And the conviction, so pleasing,

7
00:00:47.840 --> 00:00:52.128
that the people who are not
lucky enough to live there


8
00:00:52.130 --> 00:00:55.840
are indeed totally unfortunate.

9
00:01:02.840 --> 00:01:05.568
In my little

10
00:01:05.570 --> 00:01:09.300
the days of Tramuntana
have a magical glare,


11
00:01:10.570 --> 00:01:13.318
the wind swirls possessed out of the earth

12
00:01:13.320 --> 00:01:15.648
and takes the sea away.

13
00:01:15.650 --> 00:01:19.370
The gusts of wind roll
violently against the horizon.


14
00:01:20.440 --> 00:01:24.500
It is a shiny jewel of chaos.

15
00:01:29.190 --> 00:01:31.238
When it comes from the south,

16
00:01:31.240 --> 00:01:34.560
the air becomes extremely humid.

17
00:01:35.950 --> 00:01:39.518
While the wind turns the
leaves of the olive trees


18
00:01:39.520 --> 00:01:43.098
to cover the mountains in a silver glaze,

19
00:01:43.100 --> 00:01:46.020
the clouds appear misty gray.

20
00:01:47.079 --> 00:01:50.470
The sky seems to
be smelling the wet land,

21
00:01:51.510 --> 00:01:55.460
the sea turns dark, and the thunder howls,

22
00:01:56.390 --> 00:02:01.390
the falling rain announces
abundance, a greenery on earth.


23
00:02:03.230 --> 00:02:07.068
The wind of imagination
swells the sails of thought


24
00:02:07.070 --> 00:02:09.700
and cuts through the water
like the bow of a ship,


25
00:02:10.720 --> 00:02:13.640
as if the present penetrated the future,

26
00:02:14.590 --> 00:02:17.870
leaving behind a trace of anxiety.

27
00:02:34.880 --> 00:02:37.510
What happened to our lives?

28
00:02:39.440 --> 00:02:44.050
None of us had the slightest
premonition of our tragedy.


29
00:02:45.290 --> 00:02:50.290
It was there all the time
and we were unable to see it


30
00:02:51.410 --> 00:02:55.330
while life was so joyfully beautiful.

31
00:03:00.440 --> 00:03:04.320
And now, there is nothing else to tell.

32
00:05:14.476 --> 00:05:17.783
We are very upset.

33
00:05:17.785 --> 00:05:20.118
Mr. Dalí never loved anyone.

34
00:05:21.094 --> 00:05:22.877
Please accept our condolences.

35
00:05:32.911 --> 00:05:34.852
Miss, she is here!

36
00:05:38.506 --> 00:05:41.190
- Ah, hola.
- Hello, Miss Maggie.


37
00:05:41.192 --> 00:05:43.109
Good morning, Arturo.

38
00:05:44.089 --> 00:05:45.615
Anna Maria.

39
00:05:46.691 --> 00:05:47.608
Anna Maria!

40
00:05:48.490 --> 00:05:51.220
I just saw Caminada and his wife.

41
00:05:51.222 --> 00:05:53.139
Arturo is very upset.

42
00:05:55.500 --> 00:05:58.028
The notary just showed them the will.

43
00:05:58.030 --> 00:06:03.030
40 years of faithful
service, he isn't even named.


44
00:06:03.740 --> 00:06:05.198
How are you feeling?

45
00:06:05.200 --> 00:06:07.551
Oh, the leg is better.

46
00:06:07.553 --> 00:06:09.488
But I don't get out of this chair.

47
00:06:09.490 --> 00:06:11.068
Anna Maria.

48
00:06:11.070 --> 00:06:12.558
I never go out.

49
00:06:12.560 --> 00:06:15.620
But it's not good not to go outside.

50
00:06:16.790 --> 00:06:18.218
Where is Josefina?

51
00:06:18.220 --> 00:06:21.918
In bed with fever in Barcelona.

52
00:06:21.920 --> 00:06:23.978
She phones every day.

53
00:06:23.980 --> 00:06:25.228
Well, give her my love.

54
00:06:25.230 --> 00:06:27.258
She's a great woman.

55
00:06:27.260 --> 00:06:29.408
I hope she comes back soon.

56
00:06:29.410 --> 00:06:31.830
Cadaqués is like a drug.

57
00:06:32.950 --> 00:06:34.908
Once you get used to it,

58
00:06:34.910 --> 00:06:38.058
it is impossible to
stay away for too long.


59
00:06:38.060 --> 00:06:41.648
It is a magnetic force
that attracts everyone.


60
00:06:41.650 --> 00:06:43.238
How bizarre.

61
00:06:43.240 --> 00:06:47.930
I came to say how very
sorry I am about Salvador.


62
00:06:48.940 --> 00:06:50.508
Thanks.

63
00:06:50.510 --> 00:06:53.128
You didn't need to come all this way.

64
00:06:53.130 --> 00:06:57.638
John wanted to come,
but he caught a cold.

65
00:06:57.640 --> 00:07:00.768
He's in a hotel in Barcelona.

66
00:07:00.770 --> 00:07:02.248
I rented a car.

67
00:07:02.250 --> 00:07:03.970
Intrepid as ever.

68
00:07:04.930 --> 00:07:06.698
We have lunch here.

69
00:07:06.700 --> 00:07:08.563
Unless I can make you go out.

70
00:07:08.565 --> 00:07:10.722
Emilia's bought the fish.

71
00:07:10.724 --> 00:07:12.697
I wanted to see you

72
00:07:12.699 --> 00:07:16.198
to talk and laugh like the old days.

73
00:07:16.200 --> 00:07:18.938
Cambridge.

74
00:07:18.940 --> 00:07:22.620
My brother has been buried under
the dome of his own museum.


75
00:07:23.560 --> 00:07:26.570
His last great masterpiece.

76
00:07:28.210 --> 00:07:30.298
Well, they said he spent his last years

77
00:07:30.300 --> 00:07:33.178
preparing his immortality.

78
00:07:33.180 --> 00:07:34.013
Oh, what a man.

79
00:07:35.250 --> 00:07:37.480
Well, it's all over now.

80
00:07:39.480 --> 00:07:44.480
When I think, half our lives
not talking to each other.


81
00:07:45.979 --> 00:07:47.308
Anna Maria.

82
00:07:47.310 --> 00:07:48.768
You have John.

83
00:07:48.770 --> 00:07:50.048
Me...

84
00:07:50.050 --> 00:07:53.935
You have Emilia, and all her family.

85
00:07:53.937 --> 00:07:56.258
And you've had a very full life,

86
00:07:56.260 --> 00:07:59.328
and written some wonderful books.

87
00:07:59.330 --> 00:08:01.210
There was a very high price to pay.

88
00:08:02.390 --> 00:08:03.450
We were all at fault.

89
00:08:04.789 --> 00:08:08.820
Well, perhaps if you had
been a little more flexible.


90
00:08:11.980 --> 00:08:14.018
I don't disagree with you.

91
00:08:14.020 --> 00:08:17.420
We Dalis have stubborn
personalities, the women too.


92
00:08:18.590 --> 00:08:20.808
Like the strong wind.

93
00:08:20.810 --> 00:08:22.890
You're all affected by the Tramuntana.

94
00:08:24.960 --> 00:08:26.758
Franco helped Salvador

95
00:08:26.760 --> 00:08:29.608
to convert the theater of our childhood

96
00:08:29.610 --> 00:08:32.180
into a mecca of contemporary art.

97
00:08:34.030 --> 00:08:34.948
When it opened,

98
00:08:34.950 --> 00:08:37.758
people saw that a lot
of his art was missing.


99
00:08:37.760 --> 00:08:41.280
His last genius invention was overrated.

100
00:08:42.550 --> 00:08:45.380
But it has ended
up being a gold mine.

101
00:08:46.785 --> 00:08:49.658
The Marquess of Dali and Pubol

102
00:08:49.660 --> 00:08:52.290
finally decided to be buried there.

103
00:08:53.750 --> 00:08:56.920
Even though Salvador was so ill,

104
00:08:58.100 --> 00:09:03.100
he wanted to be a
spectator at his own end.


105
00:09:03.870 --> 00:09:07.910
He said "When I die, I
will be totally cured."


106
00:09:09.080 --> 00:09:10.838
Things are never what they seem

107
00:09:10.840 --> 00:09:13.333
but rather the total opposite.

108
00:09:13.335 --> 00:09:14.928
Emília, the diary.

109
00:09:14.930 --> 00:09:19.930
I described everything I saw and heard.

110
00:09:20.620 --> 00:09:22.188
Like in your books.

111
00:09:22.190 --> 00:09:23.658
I've kept them all, though.

112
00:09:23.660 --> 00:09:24.493
Aw.

113
00:09:25.590 --> 00:09:29.868
I wrote about my family,
about people I met,


114
00:09:29.870 --> 00:09:33.630
conversations and anecdotes
that I found amusing.


115
00:09:34.780 --> 00:09:36.848
I never kept it hidden,

116
00:09:36.850 --> 00:09:39.270
and sometimes my brother wrote in it.

117
00:09:41.302 --> 00:09:43.608
But that was long
time ago, before we even met.


118
00:09:43.610 --> 00:09:44.443
Oh yes.

119
00:09:45.640 --> 00:09:50.430
When he was little, Salvador
was such a charming boy.


120
00:09:51.640 --> 00:09:56.640
spoiled but innocent, full of life.

121
00:09:58.140 --> 00:10:02.770
With those piercing eyes
and that old man's smile.


122
00:10:03.660 --> 00:10:06.280
This helps me remember.

123
00:10:08.760 --> 00:10:09.848
May I offer you a drink?

124
00:10:09.850 --> 00:10:11.560
- Emilia...
- No, no, no, gracias.


125
00:10:12.490 --> 00:10:15.850
Figueres was a bright, extrovert town.

126
00:10:16.860 --> 00:10:19.398
Cultured, great intellectual curiosity,

127
00:10:19.400 --> 00:10:21.658
not provincial in the slightest.

128
00:10:31.192 --> 00:10:34.353
Watch how the dancers

129
00:10:34.355 --> 00:10:35.188
count and divide the Sardana steps.

130
00:10:36.571 --> 00:10:38.929
These are republicans.

131
00:10:38.931 --> 00:10:41.014
The author never ceased
joking about the Borbouns.


132
00:10:41.016 --> 00:10:41.849
Great!

133
00:10:43.056 --> 00:10:45.261
In Figueres we have always the best.

134
00:10:45.263 --> 00:10:46.300
Isn't it, Mr. Dalí?

135
00:10:46.302 --> 00:10:47.135
Of course, Mr. Mayor!

136
00:10:49.585 --> 00:10:51.333
You have to learn how to outline

137
00:10:51.335 --> 00:10:53.676
the geometry of music.

138
00:10:55.321 --> 00:10:56.977
Thanks to the Catalan goverment,

139
00:10:56.979 --> 00:10:59.002
all villages have police,

140
00:10:59.004 --> 00:11:02.050
schools, libraries, telephone...

141
00:11:02.052 --> 00:11:03.652
And the road to Cadaqués!

142
00:11:04.792 --> 00:11:06.224
Sure.

143
00:11:06.226 --> 00:11:07.674
And the harbours and technological

144
00:11:07.676 --> 00:11:09.976
teachings for the industry.

145
00:11:20.577 --> 00:11:25.516
Cadaqués was paradise for us
during the summer holidays.


146
00:11:25.518 --> 00:11:29.468
We spent all winter
longing for this light,


147
00:11:29.470 --> 00:11:31.303
these rocks, this sea.

148
00:11:33.562 --> 00:11:36.979
A paradise that's always been with you.

149
00:11:38.410 --> 00:11:42.074
I haven't left it in 50 years.

150
00:11:42.076 --> 00:11:47.076
We settled here for the whole
summer, after the solstice.


151
00:11:47.620 --> 00:11:51.113
When the sea was calm, we
could see our reflections


152
00:11:51.115 --> 00:11:53.520
crystal clear in the water.

153
00:11:56.905 --> 00:12:00.889
Take a good look at the stars.

154
00:12:00.891 --> 00:12:02.289
Do you see the Great Bear?

155
00:12:02.291 --> 00:12:04.408
And the Great Plough?

156
00:12:04.410 --> 00:12:05.241
Look in the middle,

157
00:12:05.243 --> 00:12:06.399
that's the Little Dipper.

158
00:12:06.401 --> 00:12:07.234
Ursa Minor.

159
00:12:08.886 --> 00:12:09.717
Hey...

160
00:12:09.719 --> 00:12:11.852
Always look at the sky.

161
00:12:13.302 --> 00:12:15.185
You will know where you are.

162
00:12:36.422 --> 00:12:38.865
Which ones are from Figueres?

163
00:12:38.867 --> 00:12:41.891
Didn't you leave those so beautiful?

164
00:12:46.816 --> 00:12:49.374
Salvador was my idol.

165
00:12:50.410 --> 00:12:53.743
I was an only child, but I understand.

166
00:12:55.895 --> 00:12:59.127
He was crazy for
cinema when he was little.


167
00:12:59.129 --> 00:13:00.083
All his whole life.

168
00:13:00.085 --> 00:13:01.502
We all were then.

169
00:13:03.037 --> 00:13:05.433
So many projects, so few panned out.

170
00:13:05.435 --> 00:13:10.384
Even though he was so
determined, stubborn as a mule.


171
00:13:10.386 --> 00:13:13.053
He was non-stop, always drawing.

172
00:13:15.697 --> 00:13:18.721
He never missed a day of school.

173
00:13:18.723 --> 00:13:22.118
He had an innate gift for painting.

174
00:13:34.677 --> 00:13:35.508
Good day, Mr. Dalí!

175
00:13:35.510 --> 00:13:37.677
Just working, Mr. Mayor!

176
00:13:42.020 --> 00:13:43.578
One of them is a fake.

177
00:13:45.986 --> 00:13:46.819
This one.

178
00:13:50.088 --> 00:13:51.438
Well done, son!

179
00:13:52.786 --> 00:13:53.617
It is very difficult
to spot it at once.

180
00:13:57.986 --> 00:13:59.350
The boy has a big future!

181
00:14:04.662 --> 00:14:08.436
At 17, Salvador was
already a star in Figueres.


182
00:14:08.438 --> 00:14:11.177
Father gave him everything.

183
00:14:11.179 --> 00:14:13.382
Salvador always wanted the best paint,

184
00:14:13.384 --> 00:14:16.779
the best canvas, sable brushes.

185
00:14:16.781 --> 00:14:19.241
He was very spoiled.

186
00:14:19.243 --> 00:14:20.243
Protected.

187
00:14:21.114 --> 00:14:23.941
We recognized his talent very early on.

188
00:14:23.943 --> 00:14:28.943
Father helped him to exhibit,
the press was very generous.


189
00:14:29.224 --> 00:14:31.455
The Town Hall commissioned
him to make a float


190
00:14:31.457 --> 00:14:33.583
for the Three Kings parade.

191
00:14:33.585 --> 00:14:35.783
His mind was very active.

192
00:14:35.785 --> 00:14:39.952
And so full of joy, oh.

193
00:14:42.384 --> 00:14:44.823
Do you want something, Miss?

194
00:14:44.825 --> 00:14:46.266
No, thanks.

195
00:14:47.203 --> 00:14:48.036
Oh Maggie.

196
00:14:53.879 --> 00:14:55.462
Such times, Maggie.

197
00:14:57.819 --> 00:15:01.152
Salvador so generous, loved by everyone.

198
00:15:07.418 --> 00:15:09.816
And not the slightest notion
of the value of money.


199
00:15:09.818 --> 00:15:11.730
It's hard to believe that, isn't it?

200
00:15:11.732 --> 00:15:14.156
Gala and all those vultures around him

201
00:15:14.158 --> 00:15:16.241
took care of the dollars.

202
00:15:17.326 --> 00:15:20.326
None of us had
any idea of the drama

203
00:15:21.293 --> 00:15:24.126
that was welling up in our family.

204
00:15:24.974 --> 00:15:28.724
You didn't know or
you didn't want to know.


205
00:15:29.706 --> 00:15:31.789
Sometimes it's difficult.

206
00:15:32.837 --> 00:15:33.795
Our mother.

207
00:15:37.095 --> 00:15:37.926
The boy has made a great float

208
00:15:37.928 --> 00:15:39.428
for the cavalcade.

209
00:15:40.859 --> 00:15:43.442
At home, he was always the boy.

210
00:15:45.339 --> 00:15:48.253
Everybody is totally amazed.

211
00:15:48.255 --> 00:15:50.672
In 1921, tragedy embraced us.

212
00:15:57.367 --> 00:16:00.174
When he finished high
school, Father decided


213
00:16:00.176 --> 00:16:04.604
Salvador would study at San
Fernando Academy in Madrid.


214
00:16:04.606 --> 00:16:06.154
If you want to be a painter

215
00:16:06.156 --> 00:16:06.989
there's no need to dress up like that.

216
00:16:08.056 --> 00:16:09.695
He is an artist, father!

217
00:16:09.697 --> 00:16:11.278
In July, neither woman nor snail.

218
00:16:11.280 --> 00:16:13.930
In August, neither woman nor wine.

219
00:16:15.856 --> 00:16:19.435
That was where one qualified
to be a drawing teacher,


220
00:16:19.437 --> 00:16:23.119
a way of being
able to earn a living.

221
00:16:23.121 --> 00:16:27.538
And so, the three of us,
Father, Salvador, and myself


222
00:16:28.681 --> 00:16:30.264
set off for Madrid.

223
00:16:31.585 --> 00:16:33.668
Look, all of us in black.

224
00:16:35.237 --> 00:16:37.367
Salvador so dressed up.

225
00:16:37.369 --> 00:16:39.426
What style.

226
00:16:39.428 --> 00:16:44.258
He couldn't, even if he'd
wanted to, go unnoticed.


227
00:16:44.260 --> 00:16:48.260
A genius, egocentric, but
I admired him so much.


228
00:16:50.556 --> 00:16:51.973
What sideburns.

229
00:16:53.249 --> 00:16:56.494
Looks like something
out the '60s.


230
00:16:56.496 --> 00:16:58.724
Now, don't stop talking.

231
00:16:58.726 --> 00:17:00.625
I like to take photos.

232
00:17:00.627 --> 00:17:02.474
Everyone laughed at us.

233
00:17:02.476 --> 00:17:06.234
You have no idea how embarrassed I was.

234
00:17:06.236 --> 00:17:09.550
Madrid, just such small
provincial mentality.


235
00:17:09.552 --> 00:17:11.321
And when we arrived, we looked as though

236
00:17:11.323 --> 00:17:15.050
we had walked out of an
American gangster movie.


237
00:17:15.052 --> 00:17:17.421
I was afraid people were
going to throw rocks at us.


238
00:17:18.728 --> 00:17:19.699
That's an exaggeration.

239
00:17:19.701 --> 00:17:20.778
No, it's true.

240
00:17:20.780 --> 00:17:24.164
Father always said you couldn't
go anywhere with Salvador.


241
00:17:24.166 --> 00:17:27.070
He passed the exam into the Academy,

242
00:17:27.072 --> 00:17:30.822
and he went to live in
the Student Residency.


243
00:17:34.444 --> 00:17:36.994
The much acclaimed Madrid Residency.

244
00:17:36.996 --> 00:17:39.778
He became a star immediately.

245
00:17:39.780 --> 00:17:42.704
Are you sure I can't get
you something to drink?


246
00:17:44.623 --> 00:17:46.787
I feel very lonely but my drawings

247
00:17:46.789 --> 00:17:48.380
are very well received.

248
00:17:48.382 --> 00:17:49.696
Pepin Bello showed them

249
00:17:49.698 --> 00:17:52.138
to our companions at the Residency.

250
00:17:52.140 --> 00:17:53.988
I wouldn't have even dared

251
00:17:53.990 --> 00:17:55.369
to take them out of my room.

252
00:17:55.371 --> 00:17:56.936
I have set myself a goal,

253
00:17:56.938 --> 00:17:57.771
I have a very clear idea.

254
00:17:59.911 --> 00:18:00.884
My aesthetic ideal.

255
00:18:00.886 --> 00:18:02.867
is to make a painting composed

256
00:18:02.869 --> 00:18:05.103
of both ancient and modern,

257
00:18:05.105 --> 00:18:06.511
merging the art of masters

258
00:18:06.513 --> 00:18:08.272
of Impressionism

259
00:18:08.274 --> 00:18:09.763
and keep the drawing and security

260
00:18:09.765 --> 00:18:11.554
of the ancients,

261
00:18:11.556 --> 00:18:12.962
taking from the moderns

262
00:18:12.964 --> 00:18:14.784
colour and light.

263
00:18:14.786 --> 00:18:16.584
The structure of Cézanne

264
00:18:16.586 --> 00:18:18.578
and Michelangelo.

265
00:18:21.405 --> 00:18:23.344
At 'The Poplar Hill',

266
00:18:23.346 --> 00:18:25.057
as this place is known,

267
00:18:25.059 --> 00:18:27.223
there is an amazing atmosphere,

268
00:18:27.225 --> 00:18:29.265
people from all over Spain.

269
00:18:29.267 --> 00:18:30.823
The majority are liberal,

270
00:18:30.825 --> 00:18:34.031
progressive and anti-monarchy.

271
00:18:34.033 --> 00:18:35.147
That pleases me greatly."

272
00:18:35.149 --> 00:18:37.398
But what about the Federalists?

273
00:18:37.400 --> 00:18:38.815
Does he talk about Federalism?

274
00:18:38.817 --> 00:18:40.351
I don't see it.

275
00:18:40.353 --> 00:18:41.542
Or Catalanism?

276
00:18:41.544 --> 00:18:42.936
That neither.

277
00:18:43.991 --> 00:18:45.905
Madrid, Madrid.

278
00:18:45.907 --> 00:18:47.313
Very progressive but...

279
00:18:47.315 --> 00:18:49.172
There's an Andalucian organizing

280
00:18:49.174 --> 00:18:51.676
tremendous poetic competitions,

281
00:18:51.678 --> 00:18:52.509
who also recites, sings

282
00:18:52.511 --> 00:18:55.469
and plays the guitar and piano.

283
00:18:55.471 --> 00:18:58.543
His name is Federico García Lorca

284
00:18:58.545 --> 00:19:00.959
and he is very talented.

285
00:19:00.961 --> 00:19:01.792
There are also some

286
00:19:01.794 --> 00:19:03.462
studying science...

287
00:19:03.464 --> 00:19:05.470
It's like Oxford or Cambridge

288
00:19:05.472 --> 00:19:06.715
but in Madrid!

289
00:19:07.980 --> 00:19:09.438
What a boy...

290
00:19:09.440 --> 00:19:11.724
Look what he says, grandmother!

291
00:19:11.726 --> 00:19:14.209
Sideburns is dead!

292
00:19:17.084 --> 00:19:18.715
He has changed a lot.

293
00:19:18.717 --> 00:19:21.474
Stopping making a fool of himself.

294
00:19:21.476 --> 00:19:22.717
That's an improvement!

295
00:19:31.769 --> 00:19:36.686
And soon there were two beloved
ones missing from our home.


296
00:19:39.273 --> 00:19:42.752
It was not long, and it
was my mother's wish,


297
00:19:42.754 --> 00:19:47.004
before my father married
Aunt Catalina, her sister,


298
00:19:48.047 --> 00:19:50.630
our second dear mother forever.

299
00:19:53.527 --> 00:19:58.018
Luckily, Salvador came
home early that summer.


300
00:19:58.020 --> 00:19:59.937
He was a comfort to me.

301
00:20:02.013 --> 00:20:03.558
Believe me!

302
00:20:03.560 --> 00:20:05.853
The residency...

303
00:20:05.855 --> 00:20:06.878
There is no need

304
00:20:06.880 --> 00:20:08.597
for so much affectation.

305
00:20:09.559 --> 00:20:11.438
We notaries are serious people.

306
00:20:11.440 --> 00:20:15.762
All right, so the residency...

307
00:20:16.597 --> 00:20:18.841
is a totally separate world,

308
00:20:18.843 --> 00:20:23.258
a window to universal culture.

309
00:20:23.260 --> 00:20:24.798
There are magnificent people.

310
00:20:24.800 --> 00:20:27.025
You were very lucky to get in.

311
00:20:27.027 --> 00:20:29.783
Falla, Valle Inclán, 
Ortega y Gasset,

312
00:20:29.785 --> 00:20:30.834
Ors all come there often...

313
00:20:30.836 --> 00:20:32.619
What about San Fernando?

314
00:20:32.621 --> 00:20:33.769
And Unamuno or Machado.

315
00:20:33.771 --> 00:20:35.467
And foreigners.

316
00:20:35.469 --> 00:20:38.009
I've even met Madame Curie.

317
00:20:38.011 --> 00:20:39.844
And San Fernando?

318
00:20:39.846 --> 00:20:41.536
San Fernando is a refuge

319
00:20:41.538 --> 00:20:43.560
of conservatives.

320
00:20:43.562 --> 00:20:44.801
They understand nothing

321
00:20:44.803 --> 00:20:45.812
about modern art.

322
00:20:46.881 --> 00:20:50.079
A bunch of putrefying fuddy-duddies.

323
00:20:50.081 --> 00:20:51.839
Fuck, don't say it again!

324
00:20:53.393 --> 00:20:55.208
With Federico we laugh a lot

325
00:20:55.210 --> 00:20:56.162
together...

326
00:20:56.164 --> 00:20:57.820
Why don't you invite him?

327
00:20:57.822 --> 00:20:59.055
He'd like Cadaqués.

328
00:20:59.057 --> 00:21:02.022
That is for sure. 
And Buñuel too.

329
00:21:02.024 --> 00:21:03.352
The one with bad temper?

330
00:21:03.354 --> 00:21:04.743
He studies entomology

331
00:21:04.745 --> 00:21:06.520
and is a great athlete.

332
00:21:06.522 --> 00:21:08.537
He spends all day in the gymnasium.

333
00:21:08.539 --> 00:21:09.930
Or practising the high jump...

334
00:21:09.932 --> 00:21:11.098
Pole vaulting!

335
00:21:12.603 --> 00:21:14.301
He wants to make films?

336
00:21:14.303 --> 00:21:16.192
Yes but he also likes having fun.

337
00:21:16.194 --> 00:21:17.705
A lot.

338
00:21:17.707 --> 00:21:19.063
And surprising people,

339
00:21:19.065 --> 00:21:20.840
and hypnotising.

340
00:21:23.119 --> 00:21:24.751
Sometimes he dresses up

341
00:21:24.753 --> 00:21:25.584
as a beggar...

342
00:21:25.586 --> 00:21:26.419
Come on!

343
00:21:28.195 --> 00:21:29.359
He often goes out

344
00:21:29.361 --> 00:21:31.145
pretending to be poor.

345
00:21:31.147 --> 00:21:32.829
A country town man

346
00:21:32.831 --> 00:21:34.492
certainly with lots of money.

347
00:21:34.494 --> 00:21:36.402
I get on much better with Lorca.

348
00:21:37.917 --> 00:21:40.237
He's more genuine.

349
00:21:40.239 --> 00:21:42.058
Bring him here.

350
00:21:42.060 --> 00:21:43.683
He is always writing.

351
00:21:43.685 --> 00:21:46.135
Poetry, and above all theatre.

352
00:21:47.352 --> 00:21:48.709
He is in Granada with his family.

353
00:21:58.695 --> 00:22:03.478
I am the man-of-the-rocks!

354
00:22:29.783 --> 00:22:33.783
Just here, looking at the
brightness of our sea.


355
00:22:36.695 --> 00:22:39.945
I spent countless hours without moving,

356
00:22:42.420 --> 00:22:45.624
in the pose he'd asked me to take,

357
00:22:45.626 --> 00:22:48.668
gazing into the middle distance.

358
00:22:48.670 --> 00:22:53.337
Oh, my dear, you were the
model for his greatest work.


359
00:22:54.359 --> 00:22:56.942
Who else can possibly say that?

360
00:23:14.740 --> 00:23:18.030
Nature in its purest state!

361
00:23:18.032 --> 00:23:19.834
Long live Cadaqués!

362
00:23:19.836 --> 00:23:22.440
Long live Cap de Creus!

363
00:23:22.442 --> 00:23:24.254
Long live Freedom!

364
00:23:24.256 --> 00:23:28.639
Long live the artists' full air!

365
00:23:53.591 --> 00:23:55.132
When are you leaving?

366
00:24:01.860 --> 00:24:03.935
Summer will soon be over.

367
00:24:05.727 --> 00:24:07.477
I was in his world.

368
00:24:10.325 --> 00:24:12.908
I felt I shared his experience.

369
00:24:14.619 --> 00:24:17.869
That's what you told me in Cambridge.

370
00:24:20.870 --> 00:24:25.104
And 1923, the winter of the great upset.

371
00:24:25.106 --> 00:24:27.371
Oh God, when he was
expelled from the Academy.


372
00:24:27.373 --> 00:24:28.955
Precisely.

373
00:24:28.957 --> 00:24:30.707
Oh, such a scandal.

374
00:24:31.616 --> 00:24:35.502
Salvador had become very
popular in artistic circles


375
00:24:35.504 --> 00:24:40.337
in Madrid, his work was
magnificent, and very appreciated.


376
00:24:42.404 --> 00:24:44.652
At home, we couldn't
understand what had happened.


377
00:24:44.654 --> 00:24:45.487
Hmm.

378
00:24:47.480 --> 00:24:50.405
Outraged by the results of the exams,

379
00:24:50.407 --> 00:24:53.034
some of us left the hall

380
00:24:53.036 --> 00:24:54.341
before the President finished

381
00:24:54.343 --> 00:24:56.181
his ridiculous speech.

382
00:24:56.183 --> 00:24:58.214
The spark that set off the uproar

383
00:24:58.216 --> 00:25:00.791
amongst a group of students in the street.

384
00:25:02.242 --> 00:25:04.531
We stopped the trams.

385
00:25:04.533 --> 00:25:07.807
The police came to break us up.

386
00:25:07.809 --> 00:25:09.531
All the students took part

387
00:25:09.533 --> 00:25:10.767
in the uprising.

388
00:25:10.769 --> 00:25:12.683
They falsely accused me

389
00:25:12.685 --> 00:25:14.502
of being the instigator.

390
00:25:17.218 --> 00:25:19.623
I denied, they wanted me to betray

391
00:25:19.625 --> 00:25:21.055
my companions

392
00:25:21.057 --> 00:25:23.818
but this I would never do so!

393
00:25:23.820 --> 00:25:25.919
We were expelled from the academy

394
00:25:25.921 --> 00:25:27.759
just for expressing an opinion!

395
00:25:27.761 --> 00:25:29.461
Is that so important?

396
00:25:30.340 --> 00:25:32.144
Let them wait,

397
00:25:32.146 --> 00:25:34.014
this has just begun.

398
00:25:34.016 --> 00:25:36.307
We protested in front of the Ministry.

399
00:25:36.309 --> 00:25:39.223
That bunch of old farts

400
00:25:39.225 --> 00:25:41.912
at San Fernando are terrified.

401
00:25:41.914 --> 00:25:44.678
They will get a right inspection

402
00:25:44.680 --> 00:25:46.938
and we'll see who wins.

403
00:25:48.365 --> 00:25:50.073
This son of mine is nuts!

404
00:25:52.348 --> 00:25:55.037
I've signed up at the Free Academy.

405
00:25:55.039 --> 00:25:59.254
I will paint nudes and whatever I want.

406
00:25:59.256 --> 00:26:01.420
I have done some amazing portraits,

407
00:26:01.422 --> 00:26:04.405
the first ones are of Lorca and Buñuel.

408
00:26:04.407 --> 00:26:06.290
I am getting a lot of requests...

409
00:26:08.496 --> 00:26:09.603
I can't leave the notary

410
00:26:09.605 --> 00:26:11.091
with such work.

411
00:26:11.093 --> 00:26:12.366
Someone has to go to Madrid

412
00:26:12.368 --> 00:26:14.011
to put an end to this nonsense.

413
00:26:14.013 --> 00:26:15.936
If you want and if it is necessary.

414
00:26:15.938 --> 00:26:17.969
You may start packing.

415
00:26:17.971 --> 00:26:19.060
I will call whoever to know

416
00:26:19.062 --> 00:26:20.587
whom you have to speak to.

417
00:26:20.589 --> 00:26:22.203
He doesn't realise that he's doing.

418
00:26:22.205 --> 00:26:23.780
He is threatening his future.

419
00:26:28.500 --> 00:26:31.127
Thank you, Emilia.

420
00:26:31.129 --> 00:26:34.522
I'll send them all from London.

421
00:26:34.524 --> 00:26:37.642
Aunt Catalina went straight to Madrid,

422
00:26:37.644 --> 00:26:39.802
and soon she was able to reassure us.

423
00:26:39.804 --> 00:26:44.466
She wrote that Salvador's
work was highly valued


424
00:26:44.468 --> 00:26:46.632
by people of sound judgment

425
00:26:46.634 --> 00:26:50.216
and that they understood
his actions.


426
00:26:50.218 --> 00:26:51.146
Oh.

427
00:26:51.148 --> 00:26:53.028
Would you like to have a rest?

428
00:26:53.030 --> 00:26:53.863
No, no.

429
00:26:54.922 --> 00:26:56.243
No, I swallowed something.

430
00:26:56.245 --> 00:26:57.452
It went down the wrong way.

431
00:26:57.454 --> 00:26:59.315
No, I'm fine.

432
00:26:59.317 --> 00:27:01.691
Catalina cheered us up

433
00:27:01.693 --> 00:27:04.923
when she said that
Salvador had become famous


434
00:27:04.925 --> 00:27:09.925
for standing up to the
ultra-conservatives of San Fernando.


435
00:27:12.625 --> 00:27:14.540
We went on a trip to Toledo.

436
00:27:14.542 --> 00:27:16.740
You should have seen him prostrate

437
00:27:16.742 --> 00:27:19.876
in front of one of Greco's paintings.

438
00:27:21.528 --> 00:27:23.084
He just doesn't stop doing

439
00:27:23.086 --> 00:27:25.159
his own thing!

440
00:27:27.084 --> 00:27:27.921
Father!

441
00:27:27.923 --> 00:27:29.984
Bad things, out of the womb!

442
00:27:29.986 --> 00:27:31.534
Piss clear, shit strong

443
00:27:31.536 --> 00:27:33.611
and do not fear death.

444
00:27:47.860 --> 00:27:50.751
They came back to Cadaques together.

445
00:27:50.753 --> 00:27:52.793
He was always shut away, painting.

446
00:27:52.795 --> 00:27:56.045
He painted without stopping, endlessly.

447
00:27:57.347 --> 00:27:59.041
He didn't even come out to eat?

448
00:27:59.043 --> 00:28:00.995
We didn't dare disturb him.

449
00:28:00.997 --> 00:28:02.106
Are you hungry?

450
00:28:02.108 --> 00:28:04.673
It's early, we're in Catalonia.

451
00:28:04.675 --> 00:28:07.521
Fish only takes a moment to cook.

452
00:28:07.523 --> 00:28:11.590
That winter, he was
reinstated in San Fernando.


453
00:28:11.592 --> 00:28:12.423
I was happy.

454
00:28:12.425 --> 00:28:14.675
He had to repeat
the year, not so bad.

455
00:28:14.677 --> 00:28:17.176
Well, at least that saved the situation.

456
00:28:17.178 --> 00:28:20.761
- And then in '25?
- '25 was a wonderful year.


457
00:28:23.055 --> 00:28:25.368
The year you met Federico.

458
00:28:25.370 --> 00:28:26.870
The great Lorca.

459
00:28:29.158 --> 00:28:29.991
Oh.

460
00:28:31.027 --> 00:28:32.027
What a fish.

461
00:28:45.222 --> 00:28:46.053
My family are waiting for us

462
00:28:46.055 --> 00:28:47.712
in the village.

463
00:28:47.714 --> 00:28:49.130
They have gone to open up the house.

464
00:28:50.202 --> 00:28:51.343
It's been shut up all winter.

465
00:28:53.200 --> 00:28:54.579
Is it further?

466
00:28:54.581 --> 00:28:56.339
Half an hour.

467
00:28:57.812 --> 00:28:59.745
The road is new.

468
00:28:59.747 --> 00:29:00.715
What?

469
00:29:00.717 --> 00:29:02.491
The road is new.

470
00:29:03.771 --> 00:29:05.986
Until recently you came by trap.

471
00:29:05.988 --> 00:29:07.110
Or on a mule.

472
00:29:07.112 --> 00:29:09.196
Six hours if a bandit didn't attack you.

473
00:29:11.493 --> 00:29:12.841
Many people from Cadaqués

474
00:29:12.843 --> 00:29:14.218
traded with Italy,

475
00:29:15.968 --> 00:29:17.714
Havana or Boston,

476
00:29:17.716 --> 00:29:19.557
and never set foot in Figueres.

477
00:29:19.559 --> 00:29:21.451
Sailing by sea was much easier.

478
00:29:22.864 --> 00:29:24.866
It seems like a folk tale.

479
00:29:24.868 --> 00:29:26.993
The phylloxera ruined everything.

480
00:29:26.995 --> 00:29:28.069
Phylloxera?

481
00:29:28.071 --> 00:29:29.285
A plague arrived from France.

482
00:29:29.287 --> 00:29:31.502
It destroyed all the vinyards.

483
00:29:31.504 --> 00:29:32.879
That was all farmland.

484
00:29:35.487 --> 00:29:36.685
The phylloxera brought ruin.

485
00:29:36.687 --> 00:29:37.839
Half the village emigrated.

486
00:29:37.841 --> 00:29:38.772
Where?

487
00:29:38.774 --> 00:29:41.041
To Cuba or where they could.

488
00:29:42.899 --> 00:29:46.900
In Cadaqués life is very hard.

489
00:29:46.902 --> 00:29:48.651
There is nothing there.

490
00:29:50.082 --> 00:29:51.413
For me it is a paradise.

491
00:29:51.415 --> 00:29:54.207
Even Leonardo couldn't have drawn better.

492
00:29:56.849 --> 00:29:59.497
My friend Federico. 
I told you about him.

493
00:29:59.499 --> 00:30:01.011
He is very republican.

494
00:30:01.013 --> 00:30:02.912
The famous Federico!

495
00:30:02.914 --> 00:30:04.819
It is about time we met you.

496
00:30:04.821 --> 00:30:06.104
Welcome!

497
00:30:07.655 --> 00:30:09.236
A great pleasure, Mr. Dalí.

498
00:30:09.238 --> 00:30:10.973
I hope the weather will be good.

499
00:30:10.975 --> 00:30:12.406
The tramuntana might start blowing.

500
00:30:12.408 --> 00:30:14.050
Not too much, a little.

501
00:30:14.052 --> 00:30:15.625
It's the wind from the North.

502
00:30:15.627 --> 00:30:17.259
Don't bother him, auntie.

503
00:30:17.261 --> 00:30:18.717
Don't worry about your luggage,

504
00:30:18.719 --> 00:30:20.844
the servant will take it to your room.

505
00:30:21.769 --> 00:30:23.904
I hope you've got a good appetite.

506
00:30:28.468 --> 00:30:31.704
I shall never forget that day.

507
00:30:31.706 --> 00:30:34.539
We laughed so much during the meal

508
00:30:35.526 --> 00:30:38.573
that by the pudding, we were old friends,

509
00:30:38.575 --> 00:30:40.528
as if we had always known
each other all our lives.


510
00:30:45.976 --> 00:30:49.018
As we were arriving I don't know...

511
00:30:50.040 --> 00:30:52.984
the Empordà fascinated me,

512
00:30:52.986 --> 00:30:54.544
it is so beautiful...

513
00:30:55.437 --> 00:30:56.851
It reminds me the fields in my Granada.

514
00:30:56.853 --> 00:30:58.234
I knew you would like it,

515
00:30:58.236 --> 00:31:00.042
but you haven't seen anything yet.

516
00:31:00.044 --> 00:31:01.508
You're missing Empuries,

517
00:31:01.510 --> 00:31:04.193
the Greek colony and Girona.

518
00:31:05.844 --> 00:31:07.975
The trembling plain

519
00:31:07.977 --> 00:31:09.819
under a delirium of blue mist.

520
00:31:10.944 --> 00:31:11.775
And your curls

521
00:31:11.777 --> 00:31:13.729
like the Archangel Gabriel.

522
00:31:19.842 --> 00:31:21.448
Now you are going to meet

523
00:31:21.450 --> 00:31:22.856
some real angels.

524
00:31:22.858 --> 00:31:26.589
A sacred public secret.

525
00:31:26.591 --> 00:31:27.422
What?

526
00:31:27.424 --> 00:31:28.257
Surprise.

527
00:31:29.383 --> 00:31:31.321
Cover your eyes with your hands.

528
00:31:31.323 --> 00:31:33.648
That is an order.

529
00:31:35.251 --> 00:31:36.799
Let me take you there,

530
00:31:36.801 --> 00:31:38.167
that way you can't cheat.

531
00:31:58.766 --> 00:31:59.597
So?

532
00:31:59.599 --> 00:32:01.266
What do you think?

533
00:32:02.523 --> 00:32:04.131
Beautiful.

534
00:32:05.052 --> 00:32:06.700
Isn't it?

535
00:32:06.702 --> 00:32:08.133
A relic.

536
00:32:08.135 --> 00:32:10.379
Outstanding, but a relic.

537
00:32:10.381 --> 00:32:12.546
Like most ancient art,

538
00:32:12.548 --> 00:32:14.363
four holier-than-thous....

539
00:32:14.365 --> 00:32:15.198
It's fascinating, Salvador.

540
00:32:16.547 --> 00:32:18.519
The Easter Mass must be amazing.

541
00:32:18.521 --> 00:32:21.737
I didn't bring you to waste your time.

542
00:32:22.803 --> 00:32:24.059
You don't know how magical

543
00:32:24.061 --> 00:32:25.075
Catholic rites are.

544
00:32:25.077 --> 00:32:25.908
I am only interested

545
00:32:25.910 --> 00:32:27.883
in the mystical part of the sacrifice.

546
00:32:27.885 --> 00:32:29.226
Very well, Salvador.

547
00:32:30.181 --> 00:32:32.812
My friend, you are a Christian storm

548
00:32:32.814 --> 00:32:36.556
in need of my paganism.

549
00:32:38.346 --> 00:32:39.179
Hmm.

550
00:32:40.749 --> 00:32:44.622
He painted endless
portraits of me at that time.


551
00:32:44.624 --> 00:32:49.048
Studies of my hair falling
over my bare shoulders.


552
00:32:49.050 --> 00:32:51.800
He painted patiently, tirelessly.

553
00:32:53.261 --> 00:32:56.844
I never got bored with
being still, silent.


554
00:32:58.844 --> 00:33:00.392
It is like a landscape

555
00:33:00.394 --> 00:33:02.278
from the Holy Land.

556
00:33:02.280 --> 00:33:05.246
Eternal and current, almost perfect.

557
00:33:06.324 --> 00:33:07.613
These olive trees

558
00:33:07.615 --> 00:33:08.731
give me a sense of well-being.

559
00:33:10.072 --> 00:33:11.830
They are a return to nature,

560
00:33:13.541 --> 00:33:14.764
construction and the architecture

561
00:33:14.766 --> 00:33:16.164
of the landscape.

562
00:33:16.166 --> 00:33:17.641
Cézanne's great ambition.

563
00:33:18.807 --> 00:33:21.998
I don't want anything else.

564
00:33:23.650 --> 00:33:24.764
Olive trees of Cadaqués.

565
00:33:24.766 --> 00:33:25.958
How marvellous!

566
00:33:27.236 --> 00:33:29.144
Baroque body and grey soul.

567
00:33:33.564 --> 00:33:36.538
The lizard is crying.

568
00:33:38.264 --> 00:33:41.517
The she-lizard is crying.

569
00:33:41.519 --> 00:33:43.608
The lizard and the she-lizard

570
00:33:43.610 --> 00:33:45.871
with little white aprons.

571
00:33:45.873 --> 00:33:47.179
They have lost by accident

572
00:33:47.181 --> 00:33:48.581
their wedding ring.

573
00:33:50.561 --> 00:33:52.252
Oh, their little ring of lead!

574
00:33:53.806 --> 00:33:55.381
Oh, their little leaded ring!

575
00:33:58.213 --> 00:34:00.177
A big sky without people

576
00:34:00.179 --> 00:34:02.704
rides the birds in its globe.

577
00:34:05.132 --> 00:34:07.132
Ole, Federiquito, ole.

578
00:34:09.279 --> 00:34:13.862
I close my eyes and I can
see him in the olive grove.


579
00:34:16.627 --> 00:34:18.110
You were...

580
00:34:18.112 --> 00:34:19.653
I was happy.

581
00:34:19.655 --> 00:34:21.083
Why don't we go for a stroll?

582
00:34:21.085 --> 00:34:23.002
I don't want to see people.

583
00:34:23.004 --> 00:34:26.570
Anna Maria, just to stretch your legs.

584
00:34:30.092 --> 00:34:32.016
You have a car.

585
00:34:32.018 --> 00:34:36.268
I go through life either
in first class or third,


586
00:34:38.090 --> 00:34:39.758
but never in second.

587
00:35:13.354 --> 00:35:14.185
They look nice here.

588
00:35:14.187 --> 00:35:17.437
- You don't mind, do you?
- Oh Anna Maria.


589
00:35:18.898 --> 00:35:22.815
See you soon, father!

590
00:35:28.670 --> 00:35:29.845
Stop it, Maggie.

591
00:35:29.847 --> 00:35:33.817
John is going to love these.

592
00:35:33.819 --> 00:35:36.852
I'll send copies to Josefina as well.

593
00:35:36.854 --> 00:35:40.604
Salvador painted this,
over and over again.


594
00:35:42.535 --> 00:35:45.035
My brother was a born painter,

595
00:35:46.190 --> 00:35:49.345
just as Lorca was a born poet.

596
00:35:49.347 --> 00:35:51.992
It was their destiny.

