00:36:39.107 --> 00:36:40.178
Bravo.

614
00:36:40.180 --> 00:36:43.583
- Bravo.
- Bravo.


615
00:36:43.585 --> 00:36:44.446
Bravo.

616
00:36:44.448 --> 00:36:46.980
In the music of dawn

617
00:36:46.982 --> 00:36:49.775
my burdened heart

618
00:36:49.777 --> 00:36:51.758
aches from its loves

619
00:36:51.760 --> 00:36:53.851
and dreams of distances.

620
00:36:55.174 --> 00:36:57.372
Dawn's light brings

621
00:36:57.374 --> 00:36:59.472
seedbeds of longings

622
00:36:59.474 --> 00:37:01.530
and the eyeless sadness

623
00:37:01.532 --> 00:37:04.542
of the core of my soul...

624
00:37:04.544 --> 00:37:07.499
What would I do in these fields

625
00:37:07.501 --> 00:37:09.634
collecting nests and twigs,

626
00:37:10.534 --> 00:37:12.540
surrounded by the aurore

627
00:37:12.542 --> 00:37:14.760
and the soul filled by night!

628
00:37:14.762 --> 00:37:17.451
What would I do
if I had your eyes

629
00:37:17.453 --> 00:37:18.896
dead to the clear light

630
00:37:18.898 --> 00:37:21.862
and if my flesh
did not have to feel

631
00:37:21.864 --> 00:37:24.547
the heat of your gaze!

632
00:37:33.885 --> 00:37:36.385
His poems are unforgettable.

633
00:37:38.121 --> 00:37:42.538
He was a mischievous,
helpless, and fragile creature.


634
00:37:45.610 --> 00:37:46.693
Anna Maria.

635
00:41:03.978 --> 00:41:06.998
Isn't Tudela where the Club Med is?

636
00:41:07.000 --> 00:41:08.833
Yes, an desecration.

637
00:41:11.216 --> 00:41:13.383
What a disaster.

638
00:41:13.385 --> 00:41:15.287
It must have been so beautiful.

639
00:41:18.985 --> 00:41:23.985
You know, I have no idea
what they talked about together


640
00:41:24.351 --> 00:41:25.434
all the time.

641
00:41:27.510 --> 00:41:31.760
I don't even know if Salvador
had the faintest idea


642
00:41:32.886 --> 00:41:35.524
that these ancient rocks

643
00:41:35.526 --> 00:41:38.859
would continue to inhabit his paintings,

644
00:41:40.392 --> 00:41:43.277
even his most innovative work.

645
00:41:43.279 --> 00:41:45.678
Well, perhaps they
spoke of other things.


646
00:41:45.680 --> 00:41:50.180
Federico was elegance
personified, such eyes, voice.


647
00:41:51.336 --> 00:41:54.899
- He obviously captivated you.
- All of us.


648
00:41:54.901 --> 00:41:59.901
Salvador and Federico, so
different, but getting on so well.


649
00:42:00.336 --> 00:42:03.045
They were more than friends,
they were like brothers.


650
00:42:03.047 --> 00:42:06.168
They loved each other so much.

651
00:42:06.170 --> 00:42:09.755
Perhaps one more than the other.

652
00:42:09.757 --> 00:42:11.761
Well, in a few years,

653
00:42:11.763 --> 00:42:15.596
it became apparent that
the love was a mirage.


654
00:42:17.231 --> 00:42:19.950
I have the keys to this house.

655
00:42:19.952 --> 00:42:22.948
Let's go in, wait till
you see the terrace.


656
00:42:22.950 --> 00:42:24.432
What does that mean?

657
00:42:24.434 --> 00:42:26.767
Um, enough, I have enough.

658
00:42:28.465 --> 00:42:30.499
That's a double meaning.

659
00:43:27.175 --> 00:43:29.201
Look what became of the shack.

660
00:43:29.203 --> 00:43:31.334
The house of the eggs.

661
00:43:31.336 --> 00:43:34.634
Ever since he went to Pubol,

662
00:43:34.636 --> 00:43:37.053
God knows what's left inside.

663
00:43:37.995 --> 00:43:39.558
What do you mean?

664
00:43:39.560 --> 00:43:41.065
A certain someone

665
00:43:41.067 --> 00:43:44.900
took absolutely everything
he wanted to Paris.


666
00:43:47.640 --> 00:43:51.473
But wasn't
anybody to control this?


667
00:43:52.621 --> 00:43:56.891
It was a way to swell the
coffers of the black market.


668
00:43:56.893 --> 00:44:00.257
Cadaques lives up to its
reputation for smuggling


669
00:44:00.259 --> 00:44:01.943
and double dealing.

670
00:44:01.945 --> 00:44:05.351
One day flocks of people
will be coming here in coaches.


671
00:44:07.033 --> 00:44:10.366
When Salvador heard of Lorca's murder,

672
00:44:14.562 --> 00:44:16.562
do you know what he did?

673
00:44:18.596 --> 00:44:20.096
He shouted, "Ole."

674
00:44:21.524 --> 00:44:24.714
- Oh good lord.
- It was disgusting.


675
00:44:24.716 --> 00:44:27.716
And then he tried to justify himself

676
00:44:29.036 --> 00:44:32.869
saying that it was a typical Spanish term

677
00:44:32.871 --> 00:44:36.371
that people used to scream at bullfighters

678
00:44:37.408 --> 00:44:39.415
after a brilliant pass.

679
00:44:39.417 --> 00:44:42.507
In other words, Lorca, with
his obsession with death,


680
00:44:42.509 --> 00:44:44.676
had fulfilled his destiny.

681
00:44:46.189 --> 00:44:49.272
Oh, my lord, what a dreadful thing.

682
00:45:56.195 --> 00:45:57.767
Sardines.

683
00:45:57.769 --> 00:46:00.186
Oh lord, why was he so cruel?

684
00:46:02.860 --> 00:46:04.024
I'm sorry to say so,

685
00:46:04.026 --> 00:46:08.276
but certain things even a
genius can't be forgiven.


686
00:46:09.878 --> 00:46:12.045
Well, he was who he was.

687
00:46:14.762 --> 00:46:18.512
He even revealed that
it was public knowledge


688
00:46:19.516 --> 00:46:22.462
that Federico was in love with him.

689
00:46:22.464 --> 00:46:23.638
He did?

690
00:46:23.640 --> 00:46:24.794
Oh, my lord.

691
00:46:24.796 --> 00:46:27.710
He said Federico had even tried

692
00:46:27.712 --> 00:46:32.379
to have relations with him,
but because he wasn't queer,


693
00:46:35.554 --> 00:46:39.386
it hurt too much and they didn't continue.

694
00:46:39.388 --> 00:46:41.901
It didn't work, technically.

695
00:46:41.903 --> 00:46:45.313
Well, he could say
some very harsh things.


696
00:46:45.315 --> 00:46:49.000
His megalomania always
urged on, of course, by Gala,


697
00:46:49.002 --> 00:46:52.745
who took pleasure in
complicating everything.


698
00:46:52.747 --> 00:46:54.330
She was unbearable.

699
00:46:55.480 --> 00:47:00.363
Well, if I were in a charitable
mood, which I never am,


700
00:47:00.365 --> 00:47:01.904
I would say she was a monster.

701
00:47:03.149 --> 00:47:06.316
She told Pitxot it was because of me

702
00:47:07.450 --> 00:47:10.504
they threw stones at her in the street.

703
00:47:10.506 --> 00:47:12.589
How could she say that?

704
00:47:13.542 --> 00:47:15.224
Did they really?

705
00:47:15.226 --> 00:47:20.006
Well, some stones may
occasionally have been thrown.


706
00:47:20.008 --> 00:47:21.508
Small town gossip.

707
00:47:22.441 --> 00:47:25.068
Your brother could be very amusing.

708
00:47:25.070 --> 00:47:28.987
Oh, I don't deny that,
extremely amusing, ha.


709
00:47:34.422 --> 00:47:37.589
Ooh, it's getting cold, let's go home.

710
00:47:39.838 --> 00:47:42.171
Good bye, house of delirium.

711
00:49:28.190 --> 00:49:31.107
Bravo, bravo, bravo, Federiquito.

712
00:51:56.222 --> 00:52:00.911
And that evening, the first
reading of Mariana Pineda


713
00:52:00.913 --> 00:52:03.641
took place in our house

714
00:54:43.597 --> 00:54:46.179
Oh!

715
00:54:46.181 --> 00:54:47.014
Oh!

716
00:54:48.072 --> 00:54:48.905
Oh.

717
00:55:28.746 --> 00:55:31.526
Were you really in love with Federico?

718
00:55:31.528 --> 00:55:33.361
Well, perhaps I was.

719
00:55:37.085 --> 00:55:39.223
I was very young.

720
00:55:39.225 --> 00:55:41.774
Was it possible for anyone

721
00:55:41.776 --> 00:55:44.672
to be indifferent to Federico's charm?

722
00:55:44.674 --> 00:55:48.226
My father gathered some
friends together in Figueres


723
00:55:48.228 --> 00:55:51.068
for a second reading of Mariana Pineda.

724
00:55:51.070 --> 00:55:53.550
On the eve of his departure,
we gave a banquet for him,


725
00:55:53.552 --> 00:55:56.310
and my father paid for
the sardana dancing.


726
00:55:56.312 --> 00:55:57.498
Sardanas?

727
00:55:57.500 --> 00:55:59.333
Oh, how lovely of him.

728
00:57:41.515 --> 00:57:45.165
Our Andalusian friend
sealed his friendship


729
00:57:45.167 --> 00:57:48.610
with the Catalans, a deep relationship

730
00:57:48.612 --> 00:57:51.331
with the best of our intelligentsia.

731
00:59:10.206 --> 00:59:13.716
Father was delighted to
collect all the articles


732
00:59:13.718 --> 00:59:16.168
about my brother, but he was concerned.

733
00:59:16.170 --> 00:59:20.955
He knew that Salvador was
skipping classes at San Fernando.


734
00:59:20.957 --> 00:59:23.775
Well, he'd written about it in his book.

735
00:59:23.777 --> 00:59:25.688
It was very amusing.

736
00:59:25.690 --> 00:59:29.107
Salvador made a very Trojan horse entry

737
00:59:30.532 --> 00:59:32.652
into the art world.

738
00:59:32.654 --> 00:59:35.735
He was planting the
seeds for his legend.


739
00:59:35.737 --> 00:59:37.747
He was very cunning.

740
00:59:37.749 --> 00:59:39.690
As cunning as could be.

741
00:59:39.692 --> 00:59:40.525
Hmm.

742
01:00:40.850 --> 01:00:43.985
Salvador had Barcelona at his feet,

743
01:00:43.987 --> 01:00:47.628
but he could think of nothing but Paris.

744
01:00:47.630 --> 01:00:50.830
He really wanted to see the Louvre.

745
01:00:50.832 --> 01:00:53.819
It's the mecca for young painters.

746
01:00:53.821 --> 01:00:58.196
So father paid for the trip,
a short, four or five days,


747
01:00:58.198 --> 01:01:02.198
on condition that Catalina
and I went with him.


748
01:01:02.200 --> 01:01:05.450
Bunuel met us at the Gare d'Austerlitz.

749
01:01:07.551 --> 01:01:10.998
So that was where you met him?

750
01:01:11.000 --> 01:01:14.555
Bunuel took us to the
cafes in Montmartre,


751
01:01:14.557 --> 01:01:17.140
Le Dome, Le Select, La Rotonde.

752
01:01:18.049 --> 01:01:21.799
Amazing, overflowing
with interesting people.


753
01:01:25.706 --> 01:01:29.243
Paris, City of Light.

754
01:01:29.245 --> 01:01:33.218
Bunuel took Salvador to meet Picasso,

755
01:01:33.220 --> 01:01:37.014
who hardly paid him any attention at all.

756
01:01:37.016 --> 01:01:40.115
And he was very sorry to
miss Miro, who was away.


757
01:01:40.117 --> 01:01:42.064
- Bad luck.
- Oh, more than that.


758
01:01:42.066 --> 01:01:44.507
Miro was the only one

759
01:01:44.509 --> 01:01:47.646
who was already in the Surrealist group.

760
01:01:47.648 --> 01:01:52.634
And that was what Salvador
talked about most with Bunuel.


761
01:01:52.636 --> 01:01:57.131
And then, we made a quick
trip to Brussels and Bruges.


762
01:01:57.133 --> 01:02:00.558
He really wanted to see the Vermeer,

763
01:02:00.560 --> 01:02:03.560
the greatest painter who ever lived.

764
01:02:07.212 --> 01:02:09.795
Ooh, it was an exhausting trip.

765
01:02:10.917 --> 01:02:13.084
That was some four days.

766
01:02:13.996 --> 01:02:18.913
Lorca and I wrote to each
other endlessly, lovely things.


767
01:02:22.380 --> 01:02:24.448
He even dedicated a song to me.

768
01:03:23.982 --> 01:03:28.547
All he could think about was
shutting himself away to paint


769
01:03:28.549 --> 01:03:29.966
here in Cadaques.

770
01:03:31.397 --> 01:03:35.136
I, the girl at the window, had become...

771
01:03:35.138 --> 01:03:38.141
An emerging Empordian Venus.

772
01:03:42.445 --> 01:03:46.602
Federico stayed in Granada that summer.

773
01:03:46.604 --> 01:03:48.385
He wrote to us both.

774
01:03:48.387 --> 01:03:50.488
He dreamt of joining us.

775
01:03:50.490 --> 01:03:52.990
He sent the Ode to my brother.

776
01:04:31.675 --> 01:04:35.291
There was an explosion of life inside him

777
01:04:35.293 --> 01:04:38.599
that never ceased to amaze me.

778
01:04:38.601 --> 01:04:43.434
He was never satisfied, convinced
that his sense of beauty


779
01:04:44.606 --> 01:04:48.606
was much greater than his
ability to project it.


780
01:07:23.905 --> 01:07:28.322
Margarita Xirgu, great lady,
had very good instincts.


781
01:07:29.660 --> 01:07:33.743
But her production was
not completely understood.


782
01:07:35.885 --> 01:07:40.565
It didn't quite capture
the spirit of the play.


783
01:07:40.567 --> 01:07:43.302
You don't have to remind me.

784
01:07:43.304 --> 01:07:45.342
I have a memory like an elephant.

785
01:07:45.344 --> 01:07:48.283
In fact, elephants often consult me.

786
01:07:48.285 --> 01:07:53.203
Some people were extremely
enthusiastic, not many.


787
01:07:53.205 --> 01:07:55.292
Theater is very difficult.

788
01:07:55.294 --> 01:07:57.049
You have to be patient.

789
01:07:57.051 --> 01:08:01.182
Federico had established
himself with the Catalans.


790
01:08:01.184 --> 01:08:03.999
But only as a poet and a playwright.

791
01:08:04.001 --> 01:08:06.799
I mean, his drawings were magnificent.

792
01:08:06.801 --> 01:08:11.218
In this country you can
be one thing and that's it.


793
01:08:13.055 --> 01:08:14.708
Salvador's paintings at this time

794
01:08:14.710 --> 01:08:17.877
were the reflection of a healthy soul.

795
01:08:20.638 --> 01:08:24.805
They were bright, classical,
before he was tainted


796
01:08:26.962 --> 01:08:30.295
with the breath of doctrinal surrealism.

797
01:08:31.161 --> 01:08:34.807
Overseas dealers started to arrive,

798
01:08:34.809 --> 01:08:38.327
and Bread Basket was acquired
by the museum in Pittsburgh.


799
01:08:38.329 --> 01:08:39.496
Now it's taps.

800
01:08:40.489 --> 01:08:41.792
Taps?

801
01:08:41.794 --> 01:08:43.402
Oh, how delicious.

802
01:08:43.404 --> 01:08:45.904
But, I'm sorry, 
I'm on a diet.

803
01:08:47.053 --> 01:08:50.720
Oh, but we bought
them especially for you.


804
01:08:52.547 --> 01:08:54.053
Take them for John.

805
01:08:54.055 --> 01:08:56.739
John will be delighted.

806
01:08:56.741 --> 01:09:00.202
I'm only sorry I didn't
bring anything for Josefina.


807
01:09:00.204 --> 01:09:01.804
Don't worry, she'll understand.

808
01:09:01.806 --> 01:09:04.488
I'm glad she is such a good companion,

809
01:09:04.490 --> 01:09:07.117
and such a clever woman.

810
01:09:07.119 --> 01:09:09.133
And you have John.

811
01:09:09.135 --> 01:09:10.468
Different lives.

812
01:09:11.870 --> 01:09:14.663
Yes, yes, I have John.

813
01:09:14.665 --> 01:09:18.389
Our lives have taken
us on different paths.


814
01:09:18.391 --> 01:09:22.808
The summer of '27 was the
happiest time of my life.


815
01:12:45.905 --> 01:12:46.738
Federico!

816
01:16:40.959 --> 01:16:42.458
Merci, Emilia.

817
01:16:42.460 --> 01:16:45.627
Poor Federico, so taken with Salvador.

818
01:16:48.556 --> 01:16:51.289
I should have foreseen what happened.

819
01:16:51.291 --> 01:16:55.124
I just didn't understand
how it was with them.


820
01:16:57.161 --> 01:16:59.712
But that was quite normal.

821
01:16:59.714 --> 01:17:02.464
You were too young, too innocent.

822
01:17:04.116 --> 01:17:08.733
And women look at things
from a different perspective.


823
01:17:08.735 --> 01:17:10.645
That's true, my dear.

824
01:17:10.647 --> 01:17:12.519
Well, whether that was nonsense or not,

825
01:17:12.521 --> 01:17:14.963
he certainly cultivated the legend.

826
01:17:14.965 --> 01:17:16.842
King of marketing himself,

827
01:17:16.844 --> 01:17:19.011
of knowing how to control things.

828
01:17:19.013 --> 01:17:23.430
And Gala controlling
everything, such a cold woman.


829
01:17:25.701 --> 01:17:28.951
Do you know, Salvador even put it about

830
01:17:31.118 --> 01:17:35.201
that my father was
responsible for his impotence.


831
01:17:36.206 --> 01:17:38.702
How could that be?

832
01:17:38.704 --> 01:17:41.871
He accused him of having allowed him

833
01:17:43.048 --> 01:17:48.048
to read a book about venereal
disease when he was a child,


834
01:17:48.461 --> 01:17:50.967
and this had left him
with a lifelong hatred


835
01:17:50.969 --> 01:17:52.891
of female genitalia.

836
01:17:52.893 --> 01:17:55.476
That's impossible to believe.

837
01:18:48.082 --> 01:18:50.665
Regino, Federico, my brother.

838
01:23:15.301 --> 01:23:18.634
Ole!

839
01:24:09.015 --> 01:24:12.015
Salvador had a gift for seduction.

840
01:24:14.460 --> 01:24:15.793
But the truth is

841
01:24:17.129 --> 01:24:21.129
he was concerned only
with his work, his career.


842
01:24:22.035 --> 01:24:26.368
- He wanted to go far.
- And by God he certainly did.


843
01:24:27.510 --> 01:24:30.100
None of us could had the slightest notion

844
01:24:30.102 --> 01:24:34.078
that Federico would never
set foot in our house again.


845
01:24:34.080 --> 01:24:36.830
He became more and more famous.

846
01:24:36.832 --> 01:24:40.081
Yerma, Dona Rosita, 
Blood Wedding,

847
01:24:40.083 --> 01:24:42.742
The House of Bernarda Alba,
always Margarita Xirgu.


848
01:24:42.744 --> 01:24:44.827
It was a meteoric career.

849
01:24:45.775 --> 01:24:48.582
Perhaps it was his stardom

850
01:24:48.584 --> 01:24:51.907
that distanced him from your brother.

851
01:24:51.909 --> 01:24:54.826
Salvador always went his own way.

852
01:24:56.010 --> 01:24:58.539
And now in his mind, he had
already created another world,


853
01:24:58.541 --> 01:25:00.541
the world of surrealism.

854
01:25:01.400 --> 01:25:05.056
It took him to the
zenith of his profession.


855
01:25:05.058 --> 01:25:09.225
And led him to break with
all of us who loved him.


856
01:25:10.383 --> 01:25:12.013
Do you mind if I have a cigarette?

857
01:25:12.015 --> 01:25:13.980
Oh, Maggie, Maggie.

858
01:25:13.982 --> 01:25:16.532
- Just one.
- Tsk, tsk, tsk, tsk.


859
01:26:51.277 --> 01:26:53.738
Federico did not deserve that.

860
01:26:53.740 --> 01:26:56.935
I don't know why Salvador went so far.

861
01:26:56.937 --> 01:27:00.034
'Cause I'm afraid there
was rivalry between them.


862
01:27:00.036 --> 01:27:01.475
At his next exhibition,

863
01:27:01.477 --> 01:27:05.757
people were scandalized by
two of Salvador's paintings.


864
01:27:05.759 --> 01:27:08.241
The aggressively phallic finger

865
01:27:08.243 --> 01:27:12.164
and the hand of The Great
Masturbator were unacceptable.


866
01:27:12.166 --> 01:27:13.137
That would have shocked

867
01:27:13.139 --> 01:27:16.823
the conservative hypocritical
minds in London as well.


868
01:27:16.825 --> 01:27:20.575
He took any opportunity
to promote himself.


869
01:27:22.327 --> 01:27:26.160
But he was making great
advances as an artist.


870
01:27:29.023 --> 01:27:30.977
Leaps and bounds.

871
01:29:38.137 --> 01:29:40.775
Bunuel came from Paris in January.

872
01:29:40.777 --> 01:29:44.071
He came to finish a film
script with my brother.


873
01:29:44.073 --> 01:29:48.073
Two extraordinary men,
crazy about the cinema.


874
01:29:49.250 --> 01:29:50.419
What a couple.

875
01:29:50.421 --> 01:29:52.885
But in Paris, behind his back,

876
01:29:52.887 --> 01:29:56.252
Bunuel was criticizing Salvador.

877
01:29:56.254 --> 01:29:57.356
That's because he believed

878
01:29:57.358 --> 01:30:01.604
your brother was a greater
genius and that bothered him.


879
01:30:01.606 --> 01:30:03.847
Hold still, don't move.

880
01:30:03.849 --> 01:30:05.328
Oh, that was perfect.

881
01:30:05.330 --> 01:30:07.488
That's perfect.

882
01:30:07.490 --> 01:30:09.823
And also, he couldn't bear

883
01:30:10.860 --> 01:30:14.592
that Salvador was so close to Federico.

884
01:30:14.594 --> 01:30:18.078
But he needed my brother's talent.

885
01:33:00.473 --> 01:33:02.383
They wanted to conquer the world,

886
01:33:02.385 --> 01:33:06.666
and with a short that
lasted under 20 minutes,


887
01:33:06.668 --> 01:33:08.311
they managed it.

888
01:33:08.313 --> 01:33:11.205
They knew exactly
what they were going to do.


889
01:33:11.207 --> 01:33:13.242
Yes, and Bunuel was very clever.

890
01:33:13.244 --> 01:33:16.925
He promoted it very well and
the creme de la creme in Paris


891
01:33:16.927 --> 01:33:21.177
made it into a myth, the
masterpiece of surrealism.


892
01:33:22.139 --> 01:33:23.056
17 minutes.

893
01:33:24.985 --> 01:33:27.215
That was
their genius, Anna Maria.


894
01:33:27.217 --> 01:33:29.994
The film shoot
was due to start in April,


895
01:33:29.996 --> 01:33:32.298
and Salvador was already in Paris

896
01:33:32.300 --> 01:33:35.286
absolutely determined to be in the film.

897
01:33:35.288 --> 01:33:38.539
That admirable quality
for never missing a trick.


898
01:33:38.541 --> 01:33:41.653
Joan Miro opened the doors for him

899
01:33:41.655 --> 01:33:44.155
into the most refined society.

900
01:33:45.392 --> 01:33:47.143
He told him to buy a tuxedo

901
01:33:47.145 --> 01:33:51.557
because in Paris it is
important to dress smartly.


902
01:33:51.559 --> 01:33:54.627
Was between the world wars.

903
01:33:54.629 --> 01:33:56.879
Miro was such a nice man.

904
01:33:58.709 --> 01:34:02.730
Your brother never wrote
a nice word about Miro.


905
01:34:02.732 --> 01:34:05.285
Salvador liked to make people think

906
01:34:05.287 --> 01:34:09.928
that when he was a child, he
would hide his private parts


907
01:34:09.930 --> 01:34:13.793
between his thighs so
as to look like a girl.


908
01:34:13.795 --> 01:34:15.494
That was in his book.

909
01:34:15.496 --> 01:34:18.579
Cadaques didn't offer any luxuries.

910
01:34:20.477 --> 01:34:21.988
It wouldn't be what it is today

911
01:34:21.990 --> 01:34:24.503
without Salvador's magical ability

912
01:34:24.505 --> 01:34:29.159
to attract the glitterati
from all over the world.


913
01:34:29.161 --> 01:34:30.634
He was a magnet.

914
01:34:30.636 --> 01:34:34.303
Salvador met Gala out
there on this beach.


915
01:39:50.645 --> 01:39:52.395
That is what he said.

916
01:39:53.285 --> 01:39:56.817
Very theatrical, hard to believe,

917
01:39:56.819 --> 01:39:59.732
like a second-rate Greek tragedy.

918
01:39:59.734 --> 01:40:01.401
Gala abducted him.

919
01:40:03.278 --> 01:40:05.528
Our world slowly collapsed.

920
01:40:06.728 --> 01:40:08.696
While theirs rose up.

921
01:40:08.698 --> 01:40:10.508
Well, they went to Paris.

922
01:40:10.510 --> 01:40:13.353
Gala sent Eluard and Cecile to hell.

923
01:40:13.355 --> 01:40:17.311
Gala and my brother were
inseparable for nearly 40 years.


924
01:40:17.313 --> 01:40:21.396
Yet in the end, she went
crazy with her lovers,


925
01:40:22.521 --> 01:40:25.354
and used Pubol for her dalliances.

926
01:40:28.294 --> 01:40:33.294
The exhibition at Goemans'
gallery in '29 was very good.


927
01:40:33.622 --> 01:40:36.534
Breton approved the paintings,

928
01:40:36.536 --> 01:40:38.921
but the critics did not receive them

929
01:40:38.923 --> 01:40:41.740
as well as they had hoped.

930
01:40:41.742 --> 01:40:46.025
And that is when he said
that outrageous thing.


931
01:40:54.139 --> 01:40:55.639
The famous spit.

932
01:40:56.909 --> 01:40:59.861
He wanted to project this
image of the great surrealist


933
01:40:59.863 --> 01:41:03.925
with no respect for anything or anyone,

934
01:41:03.927 --> 01:41:07.204
not even the portrait of his mother.

935
01:41:07.206 --> 01:41:10.684
And he did that with The Sacred Heart.

936
01:41:10.686 --> 01:41:15.019
I Spit With Pleasure on
the Portrait of my Mother.


937
01:41:18.733 --> 01:41:22.400
And that is the end of
my father's notebook.


938
01:42:30.468 --> 01:42:32.801
And then, Father said to me,

939
01:42:33.861 --> 01:42:37.423
"You, Anna Maria, are going to England.

940
01:42:37.425 --> 01:42:39.989
"You will study at Cambridge.

941
01:42:39.991 --> 01:42:42.555
"They are more civilized there."

942
01:42:42.557 --> 01:42:46.731
And disciplined, my dear,
much more disciplined.


943
01:42:46.733 --> 01:42:48.555
We had such a good time.

944
01:42:48.557 --> 01:42:51.546
Oh, life is amazing.

945
01:42:57.705 --> 01:43:01.288
His first
exile lasted five years.


946
01:43:05.592 --> 01:43:06.860
Who made the peace?

947
01:43:06.862 --> 01:43:09.236
Uncle Rafael managed it,

948
01:43:09.238 --> 01:43:13.333
but our house never enjoyed
that wonderful atmosphere again.


949
01:43:13.335 --> 01:43:16.594
Everything has a beginning and an end.

950
01:43:16.596 --> 01:43:19.309
Bunuel came back to
film some of the scenes


951
01:43:19.311 --> 01:43:21.410
for L'Age d'Or at Cap de Creus,

952
01:43:21.412 --> 01:43:25.297
which infuriated my father even more.

953
01:43:25.299 --> 01:43:26.568
They were called all sorts of things,

954
01:43:26.570 --> 01:43:29.749
Bolsheviks, pornographers, blasphemers.

955
01:43:29.751 --> 01:43:32.197
Not even Paris could
accept such an attack


956
01:43:32.199 --> 01:43:34.165
on bourgeois values.

957
01:43:34.167 --> 01:43:37.864
The youth of French
Action wrecked the cinema,


958
01:43:37.866 --> 01:43:42.156
throwing ink at the screen,
setting off tear gas shooting,


959
01:43:42.158 --> 01:43:44.080
beating up the spectators.

960
01:43:44.082 --> 01:43:46.091
A real political riot.

961
01:43:46.093 --> 01:43:49.189
It was the perfect excuse
for the chief of police


962
01:43:49.191 --> 01:43:52.175
to ban the film and confiscate the prints.

963
01:43:52.177 --> 01:43:56.790
It would be half a century
before L'Age d'Or was seen again.


964
01:43:56.792 --> 01:44:00.406
But Dali and Bunuel
were catapulted to fame.


965
01:44:00.408 --> 01:44:01.712
Precisely.

966
01:44:01.714 --> 01:44:04.547
Meeting you was such a help to me.

967
01:44:05.442 --> 01:44:07.229
I remember it so well.

968
01:44:07.231 --> 01:44:09.829
And it was while I was away

969
01:44:09.831 --> 01:44:14.117
that Salvador bought the
shack in Port Lligat.


970
01:44:14.119 --> 01:44:15.462
You couldn't get there by car.

971
01:44:15.464 --> 01:44:18.653
They had to transport
everything by donkey.


972
01:44:18.655 --> 01:44:21.114
But nothing could stop Salvador.

973
01:44:21.116 --> 01:44:23.980
He was becoming increasingly famous.

974
01:44:23.982 --> 01:44:27.114
He wanted to make Port Lligat
the center of the universe.


975
01:44:28.072 --> 01:44:29.919
His enchanted garden.

976
01:44:29.921 --> 01:44:33.004
Oh, to me it was the witch's house.

977
01:44:34.267 --> 01:44:37.445
And then, it was the Republic.

978
01:44:37.447 --> 01:44:39.604
Federico came back from America.

979
01:44:39.606 --> 01:44:43.374
He had become an extremely
important author,


980
01:44:43.376 --> 01:44:46.075
and he was very politically involved,

981
01:44:46.077 --> 01:44:50.099
much admired as the symbol
of the new Spanish Republic.


982
01:44:50.101 --> 01:44:54.434
Was so appalling when the
Francoists executed him.


983
01:44:56.638 --> 01:45:00.471
I only saw him once
again, in December 1935.


984
01:48:00.982 --> 01:48:02.216
I wasn't there.

985
01:48:02.218 --> 01:48:04.079
I arrived when the shouting was all over

986
01:48:04.081 --> 01:48:07.008
and my father had given in.

987
01:48:07.010 --> 01:48:11.260
So much crying made it seem
like a cheap melodrama.


988
01:48:14.283 --> 01:48:17.033
In the last 15 years of his life,

989
01:48:18.311 --> 01:48:20.561
my father made eight wills.

990
01:48:22.683 --> 01:48:27.606
Every time Salvador made some
outrage, he drew up a new one.


991
01:48:27.608 --> 01:48:29.129
Salvador told everyone

992
01:48:29.131 --> 01:48:32.290
that the family kept
a lot of his artwork.

993
01:48:32.292 --> 01:48:34.516
No, no, no, that was later,

994
01:48:34.518 --> 01:48:37.435
when he was outraged about my book.

995
01:48:38.545 --> 01:48:39.687
No.

996
01:48:39.689 --> 01:48:43.439
Salvador closed the
doors of his world to us.


997
01:48:46.323 --> 01:48:50.221
He or Gala, it makes no
difference to me who.


998
01:48:50.223 --> 01:48:52.381
Can't take any more
photographs in this light.


999
01:48:52.383 --> 01:48:55.966
I have spent 40 years
without my brother.


1000
01:48:59.881 --> 01:49:02.616
Things went amazingly well for him.

1001
01:49:02.618 --> 01:49:05.787
You went through many hard times.

1002
01:49:05.789 --> 01:49:08.872
The Civil War broke out, many died.

1003
01:49:11.837 --> 01:49:14.504
I don't know why I was arrested.

1004
01:49:16.702 --> 01:49:19.785
A Francoist spy, me, it's ridiculous.

1005
01:49:20.887 --> 01:49:24.603
We were all terrified of the Anarchists.

1006
01:49:24.605 --> 01:49:27.526
They had already killed
the village schoolmaster,


1007
01:49:27.528 --> 01:49:30.275
a good man who'd not been
involved in anything.


1008
01:49:58.389 --> 01:50:01.319
It was like hell in Barcelona.

1009
01:50:01.321 --> 01:50:03.654
Two weeks of being tortured,

1010
01:50:04.918 --> 01:50:08.457
you have no any idea what it's like.

1011
01:50:08.459 --> 01:50:11.792
I shouted day and night like a madwoman.

1012
01:50:12.853 --> 01:50:17.270
It was lucky a friend managed
to get me out of there.


1013
01:50:21.115 --> 01:50:25.365
He took me to my Uncle
Rafael's house in Barcelona.


1014
01:50:26.475 --> 01:50:27.975
I owe him my life.

1015
01:50:30.412 --> 01:50:32.829
When I arrived, I had amnesia

1016
01:50:34.031 --> 01:50:37.448
and I was unable to control my sphincter.

1017
01:50:39.556 --> 01:50:40.973
I was nearly mad.

1018
01:50:43.209 --> 01:50:45.792
It took me years to get better.

1019
01:50:48.453 --> 01:50:50.203
I was never the same.

1020
01:50:52.221 --> 01:50:55.206
The war changed all of us.

1021
01:50:55.208 --> 01:50:57.220
When it began, 
Salvador was in London,

1022
01:50:57.222 --> 01:50:59.805
at a dinner in the Savoy Hotel.

1023
01:51:01.355 --> 01:51:04.591
He stayed away for three years.

1024
01:51:04.593 --> 01:51:07.600
He certainly was in
the papers a good deal.


1025
01:51:07.602 --> 01:51:10.185
He went to Mussolini's Italy.

1026
01:51:12.850 --> 01:51:14.796
He showed his true colors.

1027
01:51:14.798 --> 01:51:17.465
He was very criticized in Paris.

1028
01:51:18.543 --> 01:51:21.916
It was as though he had no ideology.

1029
01:51:21.918 --> 01:51:23.418
He was Dalinian.

1030
01:51:24.349 --> 01:51:27.805
He got no convictions about anything.

1031
01:51:27.807 --> 01:51:31.384
None.

1032
01:51:31.386 --> 01:51:34.770
He prepared his arrival
in New York very well.


1033
01:51:34.772 --> 01:51:38.262
He seduced the journalists
with his portrait of Gala,


1034
01:51:38.264 --> 01:51:43.094
I have brought
the portrait of my wife.


1035
01:51:43.096 --> 01:51:46.263
The one with the ribs on the shoulder.

1036
01:51:48.569 --> 01:51:53.235
It didn't matter
if they were raw or fried.


1037
01:51:53.237 --> 01:51:55.276
It was a very big thing.

1038
01:51:55.278 --> 01:51:58.980
I was very proud of my friend's brother.

1039
01:51:58.982 --> 01:52:01.982
I've still have the Time magazine.

1040
01:52:06.254 --> 01:52:10.844
Surrealism would not have
captured such attention


1041
01:52:10.846 --> 01:52:14.938
if it were not for an
attractive 32-year-old Catalan


1042
01:52:14.940 --> 01:52:18.039
with a soft voice and
a well-groomed mustache


1043
01:52:18.041 --> 01:52:20.415
like a movie actor.

1044
01:52:20.417 --> 01:52:23.027
How clever of you to have kept everything.

1045
01:52:23.029 --> 01:52:26.655
He was having more and more arguments

1046
01:52:26.657 --> 01:52:30.282
with the Surrealists
and with the Communists.


1047
01:52:30.284 --> 01:52:34.387
In Dali's madness, there is
all the wisdom of Broadway.


1048
01:52:35.845 --> 01:52:39.514
He has a gift for publicity
which would make any press agent


1049
01:52:39.516 --> 01:52:42.408
representing a circus die of envy.

1050
01:52:43.721 --> 01:52:46.304
He learned a lot in New York.

1051
01:52:47.670 --> 01:52:49.022
New York was his El Dorado.

1052
01:52:49.024 --> 01:52:52.357
He even compared Manhattan with Egypt.

1053
01:52:53.406 --> 01:52:57.073
He saw the skyscrapers
as inverted pyramids.


1054
01:52:58.946 --> 01:53:00.835
And it was the only place

1055
01:53:00.837 --> 01:53:04.595
where he could sign contracts constantly.

1056
01:53:05.942 --> 01:53:09.319
Gala crossed borders with suitcases

1057
01:53:09.321 --> 01:53:12.818
full of bundles of 100-dollar bills.

1058
01:53:12.820 --> 01:53:16.565
They didn't dare stop her
as she was Madame Dali.


1059
01:53:16.567 --> 01:53:17.644
But they got into trouble

1060
01:53:17.646 --> 01:53:20.647
with the American tax
authorities, didn't they?


1061
01:53:20.649 --> 01:53:23.631
Yes, a criminal investigation,
it was very serious.


1062
01:53:23.633 --> 01:53:27.491
Gala was more like
a member of the mafia

1063
01:53:27.493 --> 01:53:30.947
than the wife of the most
fashionable painter in the world.


1064
01:53:30.949 --> 01:53:33.227
She had three passions:

1065
01:53:33.229 --> 01:53:37.396
luxury, young men with
sculpted bodies, and money.


1066
01:53:39.675 --> 01:53:42.258
My brother admired her greed,

1067
01:53:44.334 --> 01:53:47.704
the strength of her determination,

1068
01:53:47.706 --> 01:53:50.206
and her terrifying black eyes.

1069
01:53:52.025 --> 01:53:54.045
It's a good description.

1070
01:53:54.047 --> 01:53:55.302
Well, I'm right, am I not?

1071
01:53:55.304 --> 01:53:57.827
Believe me, I'm restraining myself.

1072
01:53:57.829 --> 01:54:00.706
Picasso said, as far as he was concerned,

1073
01:54:00.708 --> 01:54:04.688
Dali no longer existed.

1074
01:54:04.690 --> 01:54:09.690
Salvador knew who was going
to win the Spanish Civil War.


1075
01:54:09.846 --> 01:54:12.129
He knew what he should do.

1076
01:54:12.131 --> 01:54:13.795
Go to Hollywood.

1077
01:54:13.797 --> 01:54:15.942
So many projects.

1078
01:54:15.944 --> 01:54:18.272
None of them got made.

1079
01:54:18.274 --> 01:54:20.886
He did some drawings for Disney.

1080
01:54:20.888 --> 01:54:23.549
Who came to Cadaques,

1081
01:54:23.551 --> 01:54:27.912
and Salvador greeted with
jasmine behind his ears.


1082
01:54:27.914 --> 01:54:32.747
He did just 15 seconds for
Disney and then he was fired.


1083
01:54:35.282 --> 01:54:36.113
How typical.

1084
01:54:36.115 --> 01:54:37.410
And then he added

1085
01:54:37.412 --> 01:54:41.292
that Disney had a secret
stash of erotic objects


1086
01:54:41.294 --> 01:54:43.461
and pornographic drawings.

1087
01:54:44.827 --> 01:54:48.326
He designed the dream sequence
of Spellbound for Hitchcock,


1088
01:54:48.328 --> 01:54:50.852
but neither of them
was very happy with it.


1089
01:54:50.854 --> 01:54:54.053
Is it true that Freud told him

1090
01:54:54.055 --> 01:54:57.380
he had psychological problems?

1091
01:54:57.382 --> 01:55:00.153
Well, Salvador showed him

1092
01:55:00.155 --> 01:55:03.254
his painting of the myth of Narcissus.

1093
01:55:03.256 --> 01:55:04.879
Do you know what Freud said?

1094
01:55:04.881 --> 01:55:05.826
No.

1095
01:55:05.828 --> 01:55:08.661
"This boy seems to be a fanatic.

1096
01:55:09.855 --> 01:55:11.782
"If they are all like him,

1097
01:55:11.784 --> 01:55:14.666
"I am not surprised they
have a Civil War in Spain."


1098
01:55:17.474 --> 01:55:21.474
But that only inflated
Salvador's ego even more.


1099
01:55:22.554 --> 01:55:26.221
In Secret Life,
Salvador took his revenge.


1100
01:55:27.737 --> 01:55:31.693
He showed the great
master of psychoanalysis


1101
01:55:31.695 --> 01:55:33.920
with the skull of a snail

1102
01:55:33.922 --> 01:55:36.847
and a brain that had to be
extracted with a needle.


1103
01:55:38.690 --> 01:55:43.032
He was crazy about snails.

1104
01:55:43.034 --> 01:55:45.830
When the Civil War began,

1105
01:55:45.832 --> 01:55:50.332
I wrote to him and I asked
him if I could go to Paris,


1106
01:55:51.396 --> 01:55:53.927
if he could help me get a job,

1107
01:55:53.929 --> 01:55:56.596
I spoke both French and English.

1108
01:55:59.585 --> 01:56:00.835
Um, he refused.

1109
01:56:04.992 --> 01:56:09.325
So, I stayed here and, well,
you know what happened.


1110
01:56:14.481 --> 01:56:17.814
It took me a long
time to get over that.

1111
01:56:19.519 --> 01:56:22.936
Well, it would seem to me, you haven't.

1112
01:56:29.281 --> 01:56:32.864
Perhaps, some things
are hard to forgive.


1113
01:56:37.190 --> 01:56:40.769
We didn't see him again until 1940.

1114
01:56:40.771 --> 01:56:42.854
We were all other people.

1115
01:58:27.006 --> 01:58:30.730
It was eight years before
he set foot in Europe.


1116
01:58:30.732 --> 01:58:32.134
We knew what he was up to

1117
01:58:32.136 --> 01:58:35.141
because he sent us the American cuttings.

1118
01:58:35.143 --> 01:58:38.702
In Spain, hardly anything got published.

1119
01:58:38.704 --> 01:58:41.621
They were years of total isolation.

1120
01:58:43.271 --> 01:58:45.688
Dali goes fast and furious.

1121
01:58:49.439 --> 01:58:54.347
One of the youngest, richest
painters in the world.


1122
01:59:01.367 --> 01:59:05.841
Clark Gable, Bob Hope,
Bing Crosby, Ginger Rogers.


1123
01:59:48.849 --> 01:59:52.226
Eight years of frenetic activity.

1124
01:59:52.228 --> 01:59:53.943
I don't know where he found the time.

1125
01:59:53.945 --> 01:59:55.778
He was at every event.

1126
01:59:56.784 --> 01:59:58.348
His golden years.

1127
01:59:58.350 --> 02:00:00.483
Even in London we knew about him.

1128
02:00:00.485 --> 02:00:03.580
And he was busy writing Secret Life,

1129
02:00:03.582 --> 02:00:07.285
he wanted it to be a
huge commercial success.


1130
02:00:07.287 --> 02:00:10.143
Well, I was fascinated by
it, so were many of my friends.


1131
02:00:10.145 --> 02:00:14.509
He was a master
practitioner of exaggeration.


1132
02:00:14.511 --> 02:00:16.928
Yes, extremely imaginative.

1133
02:00:17.949 --> 02:00:22.097
He asked me to provide
photos of our childhood.


1134
02:01:07.961 --> 02:01:10.961
Secret Life created huge excitement.

1135
02:01:11.961 --> 02:01:14.118
It sold very well in America.

1136
02:01:14.120 --> 02:01:15.424
Oh, in London as well.

1137
02:01:15.426 --> 02:01:18.027
When he was writing
it, I had written to him


1138
02:01:18.029 --> 02:01:21.031
to ask him if I could
translate it into Spanish.


1139
02:01:21.033 --> 02:01:22.672
I didn't know.

1140
02:01:22.674 --> 02:01:25.323
His reply should have
warned me of what was to come.


1141
02:01:25.325 --> 02:01:27.408
He wrote, don't be angry.

1142
02:01:29.012 --> 02:01:34.012
Halley's Comet hit you on
the head when you were four.


1143
02:01:42.136 --> 02:01:47.136
I spent a lot of time making
notes about so much distortion.


1144
02:01:57.567 --> 02:02:02.067
Not even his lack of respect
for our mother was in it.


1145
02:02:02.965 --> 02:02:05.886
That was when I
had the idea of explaining

1146
02:02:05.888 --> 02:02:08.888
what our lives had really been like.

1147
02:02:12.441 --> 02:02:13.774
Cats and dogs?

1148
02:02:14.715 --> 02:02:18.272
It's raining cats and dogs in Barcelona.

1149
02:02:18.274 --> 02:02:21.025
No, here it's good, don't
worry it won't last.


1150
02:02:21.027 --> 02:02:23.790
Listen, I may be a little bit late.

1151
02:02:23.792 --> 02:02:25.459
No, no, have dinner.

1152
02:02:26.802 --> 02:02:29.772
You know I am a careful driver.

1153
02:02:29.774 --> 02:02:30.857
Lots of love.

1154
02:02:38.397 --> 02:02:40.147
He's such a good man.

1155
02:02:41.240 --> 02:02:46.240
After all, we've both been
fortunate in different ways.


1156
02:02:46.613 --> 02:02:47.530
- Hmm.
- Hm.


1157
02:02:49.020 --> 02:02:52.353
I can stay a
little longer but not much.

1158
02:02:53.258 --> 02:02:54.089
Would you like an omelet?

1159
02:02:54.091 --> 02:02:56.190
No, no, no, I never have dinner.

1160
02:02:56.192 --> 02:03:01.029
I'll have something when
I get back to the hotel.


1161
02:03:01.031 --> 02:03:04.364
An honorable attempt at self-portrait.

1162
02:03:06.660 --> 02:03:07.910
Truth and lies.

1163
02:03:09.222 --> 02:03:12.460
He orchestrated them very
cleverly, he was very sharp.


1164
02:03:12.462 --> 02:03:16.765
The intrauterine
consciousness was an original.


1165
02:03:16.767 --> 02:03:19.491
A heavenly place, like paradise.

1166
02:03:19.493 --> 02:03:23.326
But with the color of
hell, red like flames,


1167
02:03:25.788 --> 02:03:27.955
but soft, hot, and sticky,

1168
02:03:29.007 --> 02:03:33.239
from where I could already see fried eggs.

1169
02:03:33.241 --> 02:03:35.724
Well, it enthralled me.

1170
02:03:35.726 --> 02:03:38.541
- John was not so convinced.
- Aw.


1171
02:03:38.543 --> 02:03:42.721
He explains it all in
a way that portrays him


1172
02:03:42.723 --> 02:03:44.603
in the best light.

1173
02:03:44.605 --> 02:03:48.384
Not a word about his rampant Marxism.

1174
02:03:48.386 --> 02:03:51.412
He doesn't acknowledge Breton.

1175
02:03:51.414 --> 02:03:55.289
He says he is the father of Surrealism,

1176
02:03:55.291 --> 02:03:57.897
and then, he undermines it.

1177
02:03:57.899 --> 02:04:00.742
He blames Communist Bunuel

1178
02:04:00.744 --> 02:04:03.524
for the anti-clericalism of L'Age d'Or.

1179
02:04:03.526 --> 02:04:05.108
Oh, poor man.

1180
02:04:05.110 --> 02:04:07.213
That was why Bunuel
was expelled from MoMA


1181
02:04:07.215 --> 02:04:08.192
and went to Mexico.

1182
02:04:08.194 --> 02:04:09.980
He never forgave my brother.

1183
02:04:09.982 --> 02:04:11.210
I am not surprised.

1184
02:04:11.212 --> 02:04:12.230
There was very bad blood.

1185
02:04:12.232 --> 02:04:16.045
Salvador wanted to flatter
America, the promised land.


1186
02:04:16.047 --> 02:04:19.130
Selling was of the utmost importance.

1187
02:04:20.086 --> 02:04:24.086
He made sycophantic
portraits of helpful people,


1188
02:04:29.027 --> 02:04:31.728
- pieces of jewelry.
- And commercials


1189
02:04:31.730 --> 02:04:35.239
- of cars, of chocolates.
- Everything.


1190
02:04:35.241 --> 02:04:37.258
The amount of money he
amassed was unbelievable.


1191
02:04:37.260 --> 02:04:38.805
His fame, not at all.

1192
02:04:38.807 --> 02:04:40.954
He knew the way to survive.

1193
02:04:40.956 --> 02:04:43.456
It's a good and readable book.

1194
02:04:44.335 --> 02:04:46.418
A little long but well written.

1195
02:04:46.420 --> 02:04:51.337
It's a good story written by
a cunning and brilliant man.


1196
02:04:53.425 --> 02:04:55.758
To distract curious fools.

1197
02:04:57.147 --> 02:05:00.937
Now I will have a glass
of your sweet liquor.


1198
02:05:02.266 --> 02:05:05.653
Cadaques's
prodigal son felt homesick


1199
02:05:05.655 --> 02:05:08.072
for the fishermen and their nets.

1200
02:05:08.074 --> 02:05:10.824
He couldn't stay away any longer.

1201
02:05:12.207 --> 02:05:17.207
But the building work at the
shack was not quite finished.


1202
02:05:17.241 --> 02:05:20.491
I spent a few difficult days with Gala.

1203
02:05:21.611 --> 02:05:23.415
I couldn't forgive her

1204
02:05:23.417 --> 02:05:27.029
for the unhappiness
she brought our family.


1205
02:05:27.031 --> 02:05:29.509
You were already
preparing your book,


1206
02:05:29.511 --> 02:05:32.889
and you didn't tell
Salvador anything about it.


1207
02:05:32.891 --> 02:05:36.224
I only wanted to set matters straight.

1208
02:05:37.681 --> 02:05:40.681
I put on a
good face and kept quiet.

1209
02:07:11.189 --> 02:07:13.509
Our last family photograph.

1210
02:07:13.511 --> 02:07:15.511
He was working non-stop.

1211
02:07:17.817 --> 02:07:20.468
He did the sets for Don Juan Tenorio,

1212
02:07:20.470 --> 02:07:23.433
a great success in Madrid.

1213
02:07:23.435 --> 02:07:28.106
Peter Brook came to Port
Lligat to pick up the designs


1214
02:07:28.108 --> 02:07:31.887
for the Salome of Strauss in London.

1215
02:07:31.889 --> 02:07:34.389
I saw it together with John.

1216
02:07:35.477 --> 02:07:38.969
It was canceled after six performances.

1217
02:07:38.971 --> 02:07:40.295
Oh.

1218
02:07:40.297 --> 02:07:43.948
They had a great success in
Rome with As You Like It,


1219
02:07:43.950 --> 02:07:45.982
directed by Visconti.

1220
02:07:45.984 --> 02:07:47.807
I didn't know.

1221
02:07:47.809 --> 02:07:49.441
All the BBC talked about

1222
02:07:49.443 --> 02:07:52.443
was how he was received by Pius XII.

1223
02:08:48.254 --> 02:08:49.921
Oh, hello, Joanne.

1224
02:08:51.421 --> 02:08:52.963
I'm sorry I'm late.

1225
02:08:52.965 --> 02:08:54.089
Hello, darling.

1226
02:08:54.091 --> 02:08:55.174
Mwah, mwah.

1227
02:08:56.270 --> 02:08:57.794
What a performance.

1228
02:08:57.796 --> 02:09:00.708
Oh yes, he almost suffocated himself

1229
02:09:00.710 --> 02:09:01.954
in that wretched helmet.

1230
02:09:01.956 --> 02:09:03.951
You know, it was bolted on.

1231
02:09:03.953 --> 02:09:06.346
That's why I believe in destiny.

1232
02:09:06.348 --> 02:09:08.679
You'll be credited for
saving him so many times.


1233
02:09:09.681 --> 02:09:11.106
Any news from that mad house?

1234
02:09:11.108 --> 02:09:15.840
Hmm, I left Gala sitting in
her egg-shaped yellow room,


1235
02:09:15.842 --> 02:09:19.546
as usual surrounded by with
dozens of piles of $100 bills,


1236
02:09:19.548 --> 02:09:23.407
counting and recounting
them three or four times.


1237
02:09:24.242 --> 02:09:25.342
- Cheers, darling.
- Cheers, dear.


1238
02:09:28.398 --> 02:09:29.231
Mm.

1239
02:09:30.676 --> 02:09:33.715
She is Madame Dali, of course.

1240
02:09:33.717 --> 02:09:37.634
And Salvador, a
self-proclaimed masochist, huh.


1241
02:09:38.637 --> 02:09:41.759
Dali and I have proved
to be a formidable duo.


1242
02:09:41.761 --> 02:09:44.327
He entertains, 
I'm the straight man.

1243
02:09:44.329 --> 02:09:47.967
He is the hustler, 
I'm the troubleshooter.

1244
02:09:47.969 --> 02:09:51.555
And he's the creative one,
and I produce the dotted line.


1245
02:09:53.029 --> 02:09:55.150
We are a relentless team

1246
02:09:55.152 --> 02:09:58.949
with investors laughing as they
dig deep into their pockets.


1247
02:09:58.951 --> 02:10:01.577
Well, he is Catalan, you're Irish.

1248
02:10:01.579 --> 02:10:05.636
He's the great painter,
and you're the ex-army man.


1249
02:10:05.638 --> 02:10:08.471
He thrives on change and theatrics

1250
02:10:10.290 --> 02:10:13.483
while you, you prefer routine and order.

1251
02:10:13.485 --> 02:10:16.337
I soon understood what he wanted.

1252
02:10:16.339 --> 02:10:18.089
"Projects, Capitaine.

1253
02:10:19.137 --> 02:10:24.030
"Big or small, find Dali
new projects, new campaigns,


1254
02:10:24.032 --> 02:10:28.720
"new investors, new
reporters and photographers.


1255
02:10:28.722 --> 02:10:31.673
"Make Dali even more great."

1256
02:10:31.675 --> 02:10:32.949
Hey, and what happened in Rome

1257
02:10:32.951 --> 02:10:37.338
with The Christ of
Saint John of the Cross?


1258
02:10:37.340 --> 02:10:40.214
- What, with Pius XII?
- Why, the fascist.


1259
02:10:40.216 --> 02:10:41.654
Nothing, really.

1260
02:10:41.656 --> 02:10:44.382
A scandal, nothing out of the ordinary.

1261
02:10:45.217 --> 02:10:48.845
Dali was very impressed,
like a child would be,


1262
02:10:48.847 --> 02:10:50.860
as we passed the Swiss Guards.

1263
02:10:50.862 --> 02:10:53.978
Oh, dressed in their
puffy multi-colored outfits


1264
02:10:53.980 --> 02:10:56.401
designed by Michelangelo.

1265
02:10:56.403 --> 02:11:00.080
Well, I noticed a light layer
of sweat upon his forehead


1266
02:11:00.082 --> 02:11:03.513
as he knelt and kissed the pontiff's ring.

1267
02:11:03.515 --> 02:11:05.682
Now, the pope spoke of art

1268
02:11:07.093 --> 02:11:11.094
while Dali expressed his
desire to find grace.


1269
02:11:11.096 --> 02:11:12.090
Grace?

1270
02:11:12.092 --> 02:11:13.135
And what else?

1271
02:11:13.137 --> 02:11:14.700
Nothing about the painting?

1272
02:11:14.702 --> 02:11:15.533
Nope.

1273
02:11:15.535 --> 02:11:18.520
And as he skipped down
the corridor afterwards,


1274
02:11:18.522 --> 02:11:22.964
he said, "The best day, the
best day of Dali's life."


1275
02:11:22.966 --> 02:11:25.283
No, that was rather sweet.

1276
02:11:25.285 --> 02:11:27.801
The next morning, he called me.

1277
02:11:27.803 --> 02:11:29.589
"Dali is very upset."

1278
02:11:29.591 --> 02:11:31.905
So, I went to the Grand Hotel.

1279
02:11:34.964 --> 02:11:38.315
And I found him
in the lobby nearly crying

1280
02:11:38.317 --> 02:11:41.889
reading a copy of Corriere della Sera.

1281
02:11:41.891 --> 02:11:43.312
"There is no mention, hmm?

1282
02:11:43.314 --> 02:11:45.451
"What pope did you take Dali to see?"

1283
02:11:45.453 --> 02:11:49.088
Oh, not being in the
press made Dali furious.


1284
02:11:49.090 --> 02:11:51.811
"So, the pope was the real one?"

1285
02:11:51.813 --> 02:11:55.356
Of course he's
the real one, Pope Pius XII.


1286
02:11:55.358 --> 02:11:56.794
What kind of a Catholic are you?

1287
02:11:56.796 --> 02:11:58.931
Huh, that's a good question.

1288
02:11:58.933 --> 02:12:02.259
Now wait, "Not a practicing one,

1289
02:12:02.261 --> 02:12:04.790
"but I'm always waiting for an angel

1290
02:12:04.792 --> 02:12:05.826
"to tap me on the shoulder."

1291
02:12:10.411 --> 02:12:15.244
Now I was for a few days
with la signorina Lollobrigida.


1292
02:12:16.500 --> 02:12:17.642
Aw.

1293
02:12:17.644 --> 02:12:19.727
Oh, they were so great.

1294
02:12:19.729 --> 02:12:21.136
What a fabulous time

1295
02:12:21.138 --> 02:12:23.091
- we had in Rome, hmm?
- Oh yes, oh yes.


1296
02:12:23.093 --> 02:12:25.549
- I missed them.
- Ah yes.


1297
02:12:25.551 --> 02:12:29.051
Vivian, and Myrna, and Cotten, and Trevor.

1298
02:12:31.157 --> 02:12:35.324
Oh, I forgot, Alida Valli,
she misses you so much.


1299
02:12:38.206 --> 02:12:39.748
And Roland Petit too.

1300
02:12:41.731 --> 02:12:44.278
Breton got fed up with him.

1301
02:12:44.280 --> 02:12:48.054
His anagram Avida Dollars

1302
02:12:48.056 --> 02:12:51.478
stayed with him all
the rest of his life.

1303
02:12:51.480 --> 02:12:54.120
He didn't take it as an insult.

1304
02:12:54.122 --> 02:12:56.955
He said every morning before work,

1305
02:12:58.266 --> 02:13:02.659
he liked to see a tasty
cheque on his breakfast tray.


1306
02:13:02.661 --> 02:13:06.586
Like King Midas, he
turned everything to gold.


1307
02:13:06.588 --> 02:13:08.569
My brother could be very witty.

1308
02:13:08.571 --> 02:13:13.321
He said living on the easternmost
point of the peninsula,


1309
02:13:14.764 --> 02:13:16.707
when he woke in the morning,

1310
02:13:16.709 --> 02:13:20.665
he was the first
person to see the sun,

1311
02:13:20.667 --> 02:13:23.834
even before the beloved Generalissimo.

1312
02:13:24.923 --> 02:13:26.742
What a privilege.

1313
02:13:26.744 --> 02:13:29.812
He also said, "In the 21st century,

1314
02:13:29.814 --> 02:13:34.135
"when children ask, who is
Franco, people would say,


1315
02:13:34.137 --> 02:13:37.637
"oh, a dictator who lived in Dali's time."

1316
02:13:38.537 --> 02:13:39.454
Charming.

1317
02:13:40.306 --> 02:13:44.973
All that mattered to him
was that he was talked about.


1318
02:13:46.336 --> 02:13:50.586
He only lost his temper
once, when he read my book.


1319
02:13:52.640 --> 02:13:55.634
It took him by surprise in New York.

1320
02:13:55.636 --> 02:13:59.359
Other people could criticize
him and he would just laugh.


1321
02:13:59.361 --> 02:14:01.679
But not his sister.

1322
02:14:01.681 --> 02:14:04.848
And Gala made it worse, Gala Eluard,

1323
02:14:06.830 --> 02:14:09.830
or rather, Elena Ivanovna Diakonova.

1324
02:14:12.199 --> 02:14:15.265
You hold her responsible
for rather a lot.


1325
02:14:15.267 --> 02:14:17.100
May God forgive her.

1326
02:14:18.045 --> 02:14:21.216
You still seem very bitter.

1327
02:14:21.218 --> 02:14:24.885
No, I was bitter, but
that's all over now.


1328
02:14:29.195 --> 02:14:31.945
You are still here, Anna Maria.

1329
02:14:33.173 --> 02:14:35.278
You should take better care of yourself.

1330
02:14:36.748 --> 02:14:40.914
My father drew up
the last of his wills.

1331
02:14:40.916 --> 02:14:43.666
He was to die within four months.

1332
02:15:24.918 --> 02:15:28.085
His last wishes left Salvador nothing.

1333
02:15:29.241 --> 02:15:30.866
That was what converted

1334
02:15:30.868 --> 02:15:34.618
the contempt Gala had
always shown into hate.


1335
02:15:37.424 --> 02:15:41.924
I was very upset and wasn't
able to go to the funeral.


1336
02:15:42.838 --> 02:15:45.421
Salvador didn't show up either.

1337
02:17:07.135 --> 02:17:10.494
The dictator's regime was delighted.

1338
02:17:10.496 --> 02:17:14.535
Salvador needed to be
forgiven for his past.


1339
02:17:14.537 --> 02:17:17.365
My brother's obsession with the nobility

1340
02:17:17.367 --> 02:17:19.617
went to ridiculous lengths.

1341
02:17:20.553 --> 02:17:23.819
He appeared regularly on
the Spanish news reels,


1342
02:17:23.821 --> 02:17:26.160
pure Francoist propaganda.

1343
02:17:26.162 --> 02:17:29.051
What a show.

1344
02:17:29.053 --> 02:17:30.553
I was so fed up.

1345
02:17:32.371 --> 02:17:35.782
We were no longer seeing each other.

1346
02:17:35.784 --> 02:17:39.012
I was tormented by our quarrel.

1347
02:17:39.014 --> 02:17:42.181
His sick obsession with four paintings

1348
02:17:43.580 --> 02:17:46.163
that had been left in our home.

1349
02:17:47.066 --> 02:17:50.504
I was very lucky,
Josefina always helped me.


1350
02:17:50.506 --> 02:17:54.089
After two years, Salvador
agreed to a deal,


1351
02:17:56.317 --> 02:17:58.940
but when it came to signing the papers,

1352
02:17:58.942 --> 02:18:02.192
he tore them up and evicted the notary.

1353
02:18:56.826 --> 02:19:00.409
It's a story
about crazy people.


1354
02:25:53.284 --> 02:25:55.186
Oh.

1355
02:25:55.188 --> 02:25:56.021
Oh.

1356
02:26:06.256 --> 02:26:07.989
Cadaques proudly welcomed

1357
02:26:07.991 --> 02:26:11.586
the great paranoiac of the Mediterranean.

1358
02:26:11.588 --> 02:26:12.419
Of course.

1359
02:26:12.421 --> 02:26:16.865
And the hardest working
painter who ever lived.


1360
02:26:16.867 --> 02:26:20.471
Spring, summer, autumn,
painting from dawn to dusk


1361
02:26:20.473 --> 02:26:21.801
in Port Lligat.

1362
02:26:21.803 --> 02:26:25.328
And in winter, in Paris and New York.

1363
02:26:25.330 --> 02:26:29.152
And his playtime was a
fun and witty variety show


1364
02:26:29.154 --> 02:26:30.975
crammed with sycophants.

1365
02:26:30.977 --> 02:26:33.727
Yes, I am the divine Dali, Da-li.

1366
02:26:36.474 --> 02:26:40.911
Well, the media was his
playing field, wasn't it?


1367
02:26:40.913 --> 02:26:43.548
Captain Moore was in charge
of everything then, wasn't he?


1368
02:26:43.550 --> 02:26:47.545
He was the most honest
of all his secretaries,


1369
02:26:47.547 --> 02:26:50.058
and the one who made him rich.

1370
02:27:00.087 --> 02:27:02.270
What did he have for
breakfast today?


1371
02:27:02.272 --> 02:27:03.637
Horse?

1372
02:27:03.639 --> 02:27:05.723
He's in flying form.

1373
02:27:05.725 --> 02:27:07.781
He's like a little boy.

1374
02:27:07.783 --> 02:27:10.615
Or like a puppet.

1375
02:27:23.742 --> 02:27:26.930
Hmm, the savage and divine Dali.

1376
02:27:26.932 --> 02:27:29.606
Very savage.

1377
02:27:29.608 --> 02:27:33.177
Very savage indeed.

1378
02:28:09.792 --> 02:28:10.625
Ole!

1379
02:28:13.708 --> 02:28:14.541
Da-li!

1380
02:28:21.963 --> 02:28:23.713
The anguish of death.

1381
02:28:25.558 --> 02:28:29.999
No one single moment in the
capricious and eccentric life


1382
02:28:30.001 --> 02:28:34.751
of divine Dali, no one single
moment of death disappears.


1383
02:28:37.212 --> 02:28:40.491
Death is all time present
in my precious life,


1384
02:28:40.493 --> 02:28:44.160
and this is the reason
of my most obsession,


1385
02:28:45.482 --> 02:28:47.399
the modern hibernation.

1386
02:28:52.729 --> 02:28:54.629
Four.

1387
02:28:54.631 --> 02:28:55.464
Five.

1388
02:28:56.976 --> 02:28:57.809
Six.

1389
02:29:13.564 --> 02:29:14.395
Gracias.

1390
02:29:19.392 --> 02:29:22.475
I was hurt by his cowardice.

1391
02:29:23.844 --> 02:29:27.556
Because of Gala, 
I couldn't see him.

1392
02:29:27.558 --> 02:29:30.308
But in the end, 
I got used to it.

1393
02:29:32.457 --> 02:29:35.730
Joan Vehi often showed us photographs.

1394
02:29:35.732 --> 02:29:39.548
It was a consolation for many years.

1395
02:29:53.431 --> 02:29:57.109
At the Boia, Pere
made us laugh a lot.

1396
02:29:57.111 --> 02:30:01.618
He kept us up to date with
all the goings-on in the town.


1397
02:30:01.620 --> 02:30:05.199
Often, Emilia's daughter
would come and collect me,


1398
02:30:05.201 --> 02:30:07.868
and we would head home together.

1399
02:30:19.083 --> 02:30:23.583
My friends didn't abandon
me, and I made my own world.


1400
02:30:24.776 --> 02:30:26.609
Those were good years.

1401
02:30:28.047 --> 02:30:31.714
- We visited four summers.
- Oh, John loved it.


1402
02:30:33.372 --> 02:30:35.991
Josefina was doing up her house

1403
02:30:35.993 --> 02:30:38.410
and came to spend the summer.

1404
02:30:46.463 --> 02:30:48.902
There are two Cadaqueses,

1405
02:30:48.904 --> 02:30:53.571
the real one and the one you
see reflected in the water.


1406
02:30:55.691 --> 02:30:58.524
And which one attracts you most?

1407
02:30:59.604 --> 02:31:03.354
Both, one couldn't
exist without the other.


1408
02:31:07.144 --> 02:31:10.727
Salvador went from one
excess to the other.


1409
02:31:14.488 --> 02:31:19.488
He loved to sign thousands of
blank sheets for lithographs.


1410
02:31:20.195 --> 02:31:23.112
You don't know how much it hurt me.

1411
02:31:25.552 --> 02:31:27.969
I've known you a long time.

1412
02:31:28.896 --> 02:31:31.948
Gala had managed to persuade Salvador

1413
02:31:31.950 --> 02:31:34.212
to buy Pubol for her.

1414
02:31:34.214 --> 02:31:36.214
She sucked up the money.

1415
02:31:38.428 --> 02:31:41.511
Her lovers worked out very expensive.

1416
02:31:42.862 --> 02:31:47.362
An artist without ethics
tends to corrupt the world.


1417
02:31:48.964 --> 02:31:52.429
And more if he
is surrounded by a gang

1418
02:31:52.431 --> 02:31:56.492
whose only thought is to
make themselves millionaires.


1419
02:31:56.494 --> 02:32:00.143
Well, in the tabloids,
Gala came off the worst.


1420
02:32:00.145 --> 02:32:04.395
Half tigress, half martyr,
half mother, half lover,


1421
02:32:06.650 --> 02:32:09.679
and half banker, with no friends.

1422
02:32:09.681 --> 02:32:11.598
Ooh, what a reputation.

1423
02:32:13.215 --> 02:32:15.132
But he is still Dali,

1424
02:32:17.978 --> 02:32:22.395
one of the greatest figures
in 20th century painting.


1425
02:32:24.328 --> 02:32:27.078
The art was greater than the man.

1426
02:32:31.499 --> 02:32:35.166
Do you remember that
summer, 15 years ago?


1427
02:32:46.580 --> 02:32:48.224
Isn't that your brother?

1428
02:33:09.200 --> 02:33:12.303
I love walking, especially
when I'm entertained


1429
02:33:12.305 --> 02:33:15.806
by characters who annoy me.

1430
02:33:15.808 --> 02:33:18.744
They take advantage of his generosity.

1431
02:33:18.746 --> 02:33:22.167
They keep him company, Josefina.

1432
02:33:37.608 --> 02:33:38.891
Can't see Gala.

1433
02:33:38.893 --> 02:33:42.605
No, she's in Pubol, going
crazy with her lovers.


1434
02:33:42.607 --> 02:33:46.039
The transsexuality of Amanda
and the androgyny of Carlos


1435
02:33:46.041 --> 02:33:50.715
seem to be the utmost
erotic expression for him.


1436
02:33:50.717 --> 02:33:54.815
The dream of the
confusion between the sexes.


1437
02:33:54.817 --> 02:33:59.241
He talks a lot about the Greek
ideal, the hermaphrodite.


1438
02:34:22.411 --> 02:34:23.244
Mwah!

1439
02:34:36.210 --> 02:34:38.384
And they don't hide anything.

1440
02:34:38.386 --> 02:34:41.731
"Balls," said the queen. "If
I had them, I'd be king."


1441
02:34:41.733 --> 02:34:44.468
Everybody says they
both are very good people.


1442
02:34:44.470 --> 02:34:46.247
Amanda is extremely clever.

1443
02:34:48.662 --> 02:34:50.745
Mwah, mwah, mwah, mwah!

1444
02:34:52.850 --> 02:34:56.690
God forgive me, what would Father say?

1445
02:34:56.692 --> 02:34:59.590
He's been parading Amanda
around for years now


1446
02:34:59.592 --> 02:35:01.978
as if she were his new love.

1447
02:35:01.980 --> 02:35:05.755
A hook for everything
that is said about him.


1448
02:35:05.757 --> 02:35:08.094
But Gala can't stand her,

1449
02:35:08.096 --> 02:35:11.453
and has said goodbye
to Port Lligat forever.


1450
02:36:08.856 --> 02:36:10.204
Baby!

1451
02:36:10.206 --> 02:36:11.732
Baby, come back to me!

1452
02:36:37.268 --> 02:36:39.272
Salvador could only go to Pubol

1453
02:36:39.274 --> 02:36:43.107
if Gala condescended to
invite him in writing.


1454
02:36:45.027 --> 02:36:46.620
For 10 years,

1455
02:36:46.622 --> 02:36:50.539
Pubol was a refuge for
her senile debaucheries.


1456
02:36:52.430 --> 02:36:55.427
Of course, Jeff Fenholt.

1457
02:36:55.429 --> 02:36:58.118
I saw him once in the theater.

1458
02:36:58.120 --> 02:37:01.786
He was good-looking, but a mediocre actor.

1459
02:37:01.788 --> 02:37:05.656
Gala was in love with
Jeff like a teenager.


1460
02:37:05.658 --> 02:37:08.325
She was 57 years older than him.

1461
02:37:10.825 --> 02:37:13.059
Was his youth that excited her.

1462
02:37:13.061 --> 02:37:15.811
And his life, music, and drugs.

1463
02:37:17.696 --> 02:37:21.687
But that love was no an
obstacle to her promiscuity.


1464
02:37:21.689 --> 02:37:24.239
Gala was quite something.

1465
02:37:24.241 --> 02:37:25.658
What a character.

1466
02:37:26.698 --> 02:37:30.139
Gala bought Jeff a house on Long Island

1467
02:37:30.141 --> 02:37:33.127
for a million and half dollars.

1468
02:37:33.129 --> 02:37:36.212
Gala was Salvador's amulet, his icon.

1469
02:37:40.984 --> 02:37:42.983
He really believed she was the only one

1470
02:37:42.985 --> 02:37:44.855
who could protected him.

1471
02:37:44.857 --> 02:37:45.774
From who?

1472
02:37:47.356 --> 02:37:48.939
Perhaps everyone.

1473
02:37:52.344 --> 02:37:53.336
I never told you this,

1474
02:37:53.338 --> 02:37:56.255
but I saw Gala once eight years ago

1475
02:37:58.395 --> 02:38:02.332
in the lobby of the St.
Regis Hotel in New York.


1476
02:38:02.334 --> 02:38:05.659
John asked me to go with
him on a business trip.


1477
02:38:05.661 --> 02:38:08.190
We have a lot of friends there.

1478
02:38:08.192 --> 02:38:11.408
We were in the lobby
about to go out to dinner,


1479
02:38:11.410 --> 02:38:14.631
when the elevator door opened.

1480
02:38:14.633 --> 02:38:17.033
She was being taken to hospital.

1481
02:38:17.035 --> 02:38:18.985
They had had a fierce argument,

1482
02:38:18.987 --> 02:38:21.570
and Salvador had beaten her up.

1483
02:38:22.833 --> 02:38:25.375
I hardly recognized her.

1484
02:38:25.377 --> 02:38:29.119
He was sobbing, scared
to death in his room,


1485
02:38:29.121 --> 02:38:33.479
interrogated by the police, or
that's what the rumors said.


1486
02:38:33.481 --> 02:38:38.481
I have no idea why she was
brought out in front of everyone.


1487
02:38:40.694 --> 02:38:43.277
Oh, my god, the gold bullion.

1488
02:38:44.319 --> 02:38:49.319
Gala passed away in Port
Lligat, and Salvador's clique


1489
02:38:49.351 --> 02:38:53.124
decided to move the
body in secret to Pubol.


1490
02:38:53.126 --> 02:38:56.834
It was where she wanted to be buried.

1491
02:38:56.836 --> 02:38:58.705
Salvador became deeply depressed.

1492
02:38:58.707 --> 02:39:00.448
He moved to Pubol,

1493
02:39:00.450 --> 02:39:04.200
clinging to Gala's grave
buried in the crypt.


1494
02:39:05.342 --> 02:39:08.670
He was suffering from attacks of paranoia.

1495
02:39:08.672 --> 02:39:11.922
He was in the
final stages of his life.

1496
02:39:12.757 --> 02:39:17.174
I asked to see him, but
he didn't want that.


1497
02:39:17.176 --> 02:39:19.676
"Not my family, they hate me."

1498
02:39:21.650 --> 02:39:23.969
He had a serious accident,

1499
02:39:23.971 --> 02:39:28.319
and was taken to the
Pilar Clinic in Barcelona.


1500
02:39:28.321 --> 02:39:30.071
He called me to come.

1501
02:39:31.373 --> 02:39:33.869
I didn't know what to expect.

1502
02:39:33.871 --> 02:39:37.371
I would prefer to have avoided that visit.

1503
02:39:39.604 --> 02:39:43.396
The burns were affecting 18% of his body

1504
02:39:43.398 --> 02:39:46.201
and he only weighed 40 kilos.

1505
02:39:46.203 --> 02:39:50.370
He looked so pitiful with
that nasal-gastric drip.


1506
02:39:52.674 --> 02:39:56.757
We hadn't seen each other
for more than 30 years.


1507
02:40:28.760 --> 02:40:31.625
He got them to take him
to the Galatea Tower


1508
02:40:31.627 --> 02:40:34.066
at his museum in Figueres,

1509
02:40:34.068 --> 02:40:37.401
to Daliland, not to Cadaques, not Pubol.

1510
02:40:40.059 --> 02:40:43.749
He wanted to be
laid to rest in glory,

1511
02:40:43.751 --> 02:40:46.751
but totally on his own, like an owl.

1512
02:40:49.351 --> 02:40:52.666
The king had made him marquess
in perpetuity, as usual,


1513
02:40:52.668 --> 02:40:55.335
but after a year, 
Salvador asked

1514
02:40:56.376 --> 02:40:58.847
that the it should be made personal

1515
02:40:58.849 --> 02:41:01.771
and for his lifetime only.

1516
02:41:01.773 --> 02:41:05.190
The title of marquess would end with him.

1517
02:41:06.411 --> 02:41:09.532
Unheard of, unprecedented.

1518
02:41:09.534 --> 02:41:10.914
In the tabloid press,

1519
02:41:10.916 --> 02:41:13.984
it was reported that he had
been very well embalmed,


1520
02:41:13.986 --> 02:41:17.047
that he could last for 200 years.

1521
02:41:17.049 --> 02:41:19.656
The press in Madrid celebrated.

1522
02:41:19.658 --> 02:41:22.325
Dali has disinherited Catalonia.

1523
02:41:23.812 --> 02:41:27.208
Even in England, that
was considered a betrayal.


1524
02:41:27.210 --> 02:41:30.481
The Catalan President said,
"We know that we were tricked,


1525
02:41:30.483 --> 02:41:33.779
"but we do not
know who was behind it."

1526
02:41:33.781 --> 02:41:38.499
The whole lot for the Spanish
state, nothing for Catalonia.


1527
02:41:38.501 --> 02:41:40.464
Why did he do it?

1528
02:41:40.466 --> 02:41:45.466
Today you've explained to
me that you have come through.


1529
02:41:45.668 --> 02:41:47.794
Do you not realize?

1530
02:41:47.796 --> 02:41:49.379
What do you mean?

1531
02:41:50.519 --> 02:41:53.544
Do you remember what we
were taught at Cambridge?


1532
02:41:53.546 --> 02:41:56.674
Secret of life is to be yourself?

1533
02:41:56.676 --> 02:42:00.189
In this wild, beautiful landscape,

1534
02:42:00.191 --> 02:42:02.799
with all that you have suffered,

1535
02:42:02.801 --> 02:42:05.066
you have defended your world

1536
02:42:05.068 --> 02:42:09.002
despite all the blunders
your brother made.


1537
02:42:09.004 --> 02:42:10.751
I don't know.

1538
02:42:10.753 --> 02:42:12.718
You don't know?

1539
02:42:12.720 --> 02:42:14.553
Look how it has ended.

1540
02:42:15.500 --> 02:42:17.000
You have survived.

1541
02:42:18.521 --> 02:42:20.685
You have been yourself.

1542
02:42:20.687 --> 02:42:24.854
You have been true to
yourself, and that's enough.


1543
02:42:27.085 --> 02:42:27.916
From my family,

1544
02:42:27.918 --> 02:42:31.642
only my cousin Montserrat
went to the funeral.


1545
02:42:31.644 --> 02:42:33.061
I was ill in bed.

1546
02:42:34.257 --> 02:42:38.886
I had a Mass said for him.

1547
02:42:45.771 --> 02:42:48.619
Anna Maria, I will be back next summer.

1548
02:42:48.621 --> 02:42:50.226
John has promised.

1549
02:42:50.228 --> 02:42:52.925
I will spend three weeks here.

1550
02:42:52.927 --> 02:42:56.726
Who knows if I will still be here.

1551
02:42:56.728 --> 02:42:59.286
You have to get through the mourning.

1552
02:42:59.288 --> 02:43:01.524
Now you must take care of yourself.

1553
02:43:01.526 --> 02:43:03.109
You have good help.

1554
02:43:04.040 --> 02:43:04.873
Ciao.

1555
02:43:07.869 --> 02:43:09.202
Gracias, Emilia.

1556
02:43:10.308 --> 02:43:11.141
Ciao.

1557
02:43:15.593 --> 02:43:18.466
Come to London for a few days.

1558
02:43:18.468 --> 02:43:20.744
You need a change of scene.

1559
02:43:20.746 --> 02:43:22.663
We'll have a good time.

1560
02:43:25.542 --> 02:43:27.542
See you soon, Miss Dali.

1561
02:43:47.670 --> 02:43:49.003
Merci, Emilia.

1562
02:43:54.947 --> 02:43:56.847
Is there a
telephone in the lobby?


1563
02:43:56.849 --> 02:43:59.180
I don't want to disturb my husband,

1564
02:43:59.182 --> 02:44:01.562
he may already be asleep.

1565
02:44:05.989 --> 02:44:06.820
Emilia.

1566
02:44:18.848 --> 02:44:19.681
Oh.

1567
02:44:26.846 --> 02:44:28.449
Maggie.

1568
02:44:28.451 --> 02:44:30.177
Hello, Maggie.

1569
02:44:30.179 --> 02:44:32.790
It's 11:00, I'm in Barcelona.

1570
02:44:32.792 --> 02:44:34.951
I didn't want you to worry.

1571
02:44:34.953 --> 02:44:38.453
You made in two
hours, you are a wonder.

1572
02:44:40.863 --> 02:44:43.030
I was so happy to see you.

1573
02:44:43.904 --> 02:44:44.737
Me too.

1574
02:44:45.775 --> 02:44:47.691
Rest, Anna Maria.

1575
02:44:47.693 --> 02:44:49.514
I'll see you soon.

1576
02:44:49.516 --> 02:44:50.692
Goodnight.

1577
02:44:50.694 --> 02:44:52.656
Bye, Anna Maria.

1578
02:44:52.658 --> 02:44:54.158
Goodbye, Maggie.

1579
02:45:14.962 --> 02:45:18.724
The wind of imagination
swells the sails of thought


1580
02:45:18.726 --> 02:45:22.395
and cuts through the water
like the bow of a ship,


1581
02:45:22.397 --> 02:45:26.424
just as if the present
penetrated the future


1582
02:45:26.426 --> 02:45:29.259
leaving behind a trace of anxiety.

1583
02:45:43.959 --> 02:45:46.209
What happened to our lives?

1584
02:45:47.253 --> 02:45:50.170
They just passed by, and that's it.

1585
02:45:52.632 --> 02:45:57.241
None of us had the slightest
premonition of our tragedy.


1586
02:45:57.243 --> 02:46:01.826
It was there all the time
and we were unable to see it.


1587
02:46:04.028 --> 02:46:08.195
Despite all the odds, life
was joyfully beautiful.


1588
02:46:11.301 --> 02:46:14.218
Now, there is nothing else to tell.

